('129115403803409_10152584197648005', 'I live in Uttara housing complex, next to City centre Rajarhat. We don’t have proper road crossing facilities for ongoing metro work. Yesterday while returning from office around 7 pm, I saw pedestrians ( which includes visitors in CC2, the residents of Uttara housing and Ujjwala housing) were crossing roads all by themselves in the midst of the fast moving traffic. When I approached the traffic constable there to help us to cross the road, he said it is not his duty. He was quite rude and asked me to report at the police assistant booth adjacent to the mall. When I approached them they asked me to go to nearby police station (which is new town police station , which is 10-12 km away from the venue) and put the compliant. I told him that the booth they are occupying says “POLICE ASSISTANCE BOOTH” why are they sending me to police station, they said they have nothing to do with what I am asking for. Therefore I took some picture. Everyday hundreds of people crossing the road risking their lives in that dark road in the midst of fast moving traffic in Rajarhat express highway, in front of a busy mall. My request is to the Kolkata traffic control department to look into the matter before it is too late and before we already have accident reported due to lack of proper facility.', '2014-10-28T07:49:20+0000', 'negative'),
