('129115403803409_10152690991044822', 'I took a taxi - WB 04B 1730. yesterday around 3.40 PM from Medica Hospital of Em Bypass and got down near Triangular Park. The meter of the Taxi was faulty as I am a regular commuter. The meter reading showed a distance of 10.3 KM (The road distance as per google map is 7.5 Km) and amount payable was Rs 110 or something like that. When I challenged the taxi driver, he  settled for a payment of Rs 70/- and refused to go to Gariahat Police Station. This cab driver is cheating people. There were numerous wires connected to his meter. The driver, was however polite and did not used any abusive words. He took Rs 70/- and went away. I am sharing Some photographs taken in my mobile, if it anyway help you to stop this cab from cheating people.', '2014-11-17T03:47:52+0000', 'neutral'),
