('129115403803409_10153589561834525', 'Posting this on behalf of my father, Arvind Kumar Mehta. \n\nSubject: Violent & abusive behaviour by a taxi driver. \n\nWe (my son, Saurav Mehta, and I) hailed a taxi, number WB 04G 0183, from Elgin Rd., PC Chandra, Chowringhee, for travel to Sudder Str. (which was clearly told to the taxi driver). As we took a turn from Kyd Str. into Chowringhee lane he refused to go to Sudder Str. and turned the taxi towards Marquis Str. saying that you have to get down here (even though traffic rules allow us to go straight) to which we refused because I am a senior citizen, aged 65 years and having severe body pain. Post-this, he started abusing us and threatening us. Once even physically touching me, to intimidate us. His behaviour and body language, were frankly too abusive to be described. As passerby\'s came to our help, we could reach our destination albeit with extra cost. His overall attitude, temperament, and body language smacked that of a street-side rogue. Unless action is taken against such drivers they will continue to harass people who appear weak, vulnerable and unable to provide resistance. \nWe also noticed that he has erased his taxi number which is supposed to be displayed inside the taxi. We are attaching a couple of photos for your reference and as evidence. Please take appropriate action and let us know how we can follow-up with the department to ensure that action is taken against him. \n\nRegards,\nArvind Kumar Mehta\n\nPS: Please note that we have also lodged a complaint via your online portal. Attaching a screenshot of the same, in the comments section, for your reference.', '2015-08-08T16:49:17+0000', 'negative'),
