('129115403803409_10153592995087710', 'Dear Kolkata Traffic Police,\n\nAs a law abiding citizen of this city, its an earnest request to stop harassing commuters. Todays incident not only left me disturbed but also made me miss my doctors appointment. I visited Maidan market and parked my bike in the lane beside it. After collecting my stuff in approx 10mins, when i returned back to my bike I saw the front tyre clamped. On noticing further, I did see a no parking sign on the adjacent wall. Accepting my mistake, I called the South Guard Post (number was left behind by the officer) and asked them for assistance. They assured me that the officer will be informed and will unclamp my bike. To my horror, i kept waiting there for 2 hours and despite calling the guard post several times there was no sign of the KIND and HELPFUL officer. With an injured leg, I kept hopping from one traffic guard to the other in despair. Finally, was shown some mercy and after more than 2 hours, a person in civil dress came and unclamped my bike. On asking him on who finally sent him, he did not have any answer and left in a hurry. Respected Officers, accepting my mistake, i was ready to pay the fine imposed for parking in No Parking zone, but making someone wait for more than two hours does not highlight your judgement of law or helpfull nature', '2015-08-24T16:52:47+0000', 'positive'),
