('129115403803409_10153827869204710', 'Respected Sir,\nNew Year Wishes to you and your entire department.\n\nThe sole motive of sending this email to your good office is to highlight the rampant illegal parking violations on Princep Street (southern flank from seetala udipi hotel till the flank opposite Sabir Hotel) where already NO PARKING boards are put in place. A detailed report is mentioned hereunder:\n\n1. even though a no parking board is displayed outside the \"SANTOSH RADIO SHOP\", rampant illegal LCV\'s (better known as CHOOTA HATHI) are parked here for loading and unloading the goods of Santosh Radio.\n2. When the drivers of these vehicles were reminded that this place is off bound for parking as is evident by the no parking sign, they have showered accusations on your esteemed traffic sergeants accusing them of resorting to \"MONTHLY FIXED RENUMERATION\" in lieu of allowing then to park thereon.\n3. Where the yellow designated parking line has been drawn to indicate the maximum limit for parking vehicles, the traffic constable against a monthly fixed remuneration grants permission to an extra vehicle to park there....picture of the grey Volkswagen is attached to highlight this point.\n\nRequest your good office to look into this matter at the earliest and ensure such rampant illegal activities are curtailed.\n\nBest regards', '2016-01-08T14:38:08+0000', 'neutral'),
('129115403803409_10153851779799097', 'Long post, but it would be a good read, trust me.\n\nOn my way to the GD Birla Sabhaghar on 02.05.15 evening, to watch the Play \'Ek Mulaqat\', I observed that an old lady of around 65, was lying on the pavement, close to the Tiru Mani main Gate, Ballygunge phari. I observed that people like me looked at her & passed by, but no one helped her in any way.\n\nSince the play was about to start I rushed in & tried in vain to contact \'Nirmal Hriday\' a home of Missionaries Of Charity, at Kalighat, but had issues with net connectivity & hence could not call them.\n\nOn my way back, I did not find the old lady at that place & thought that she might have left, only to see her lying close to \'The Dhaba\' & she did not seem well at all. Seemed she had not had anything to eat & was extremely frail.\n\nThis time I was lucky with the net connection & got through to Nirmal Hriday. Explained the matter to a Sister who said that I needed to bring the matter immediately to the notice of Kolkata Police (KP) , because with out proper cop documents they do not admit any inmate into their home, at Kalighat.\n\nI immediately rushed to the Traffic Sargent at the phari crossing & urged him to look into the matter by getting some much needed help \'cause I felt that the lady may not survive through the night in the absence of any medical help.\n\nThe Sargent, Golok Sarkar immediately informed Gariahat PS, his base PS, and since the Dhaba area came under Ballygunge PS, asked a colleague at Gariahat PS to inform his counterpart at Ballygunge PS to send some help immediately. All this while he was attending to his job of registering cases of traffic violators etc....After a wait of about half an hour SI, Mr. AK Laha of Ballygunge PS, came with his colleague on an Enfield Bullet, and immediately attended to the Old lady.\n\nI was amazed at the sincerity of Mr. Laha who spoke to the elderly lady, as if she was his Mother, poured water on her head, made her sit up against a wall, offered her ORS & arranged for Tea for her. Inquired about her family, home & other members etc....Thanked me for being a responsible citizen & decided to take the Lady to Ballygunge PS, as it was almost 2100 hrs. I took Mr. Laha\'s no. and got to know of his plans for her medical treatment as well.\n\nThe reason I decided to share this with all of you, is that, often such acts of promptness by the police do not get registered or talked about, in the public domain, and they do not get credit for the difficult job that they are expected to do in the Kolkata heat, day after day, without much recognition.\n\nI therefore decided to document this event, which is special for me, as an experience and would like to take the opportunity to sincerely thank, Sargent. Golok Sarkar of Gariahat PS & SI AK Laha of Ballygunge PS for doing the needful & helping the distraught Lady.\n\nFolks we always expect the police to do their job, come what may, but if we too can lend a helping hand by bringing matters to their notice promptly, chances are, it would lead to a much harmonious relationship between the citizens & the police.\n\nThank you, KP. Indeed very proud of you.\n\nhttps://www.facebook.com/pages/Kolkata-Police/132989860074312\n\nhttps://www.facebook.com/KolkataTrafficPolice?fref=ts\n\nhttps://www.facebook.com/search/132989860074312/likers\n\nhttps://www.facebook.com/search/120083111372008/likers', '2015-05-05T04:05:26+0000', 'positive'),
