('129115403803409_10154761295434296', 'Sir, can this case be resolved now. I first posted this in 2015 (Refer to the write-up below). Then reposted it very recently in 2017 ( roughly 3 weeks back). I was called from for the traffic department, inquired and finally was assured that the case would get dropped as it was an incorrect tagging of the incident to my car. I still see the case to be there on your portal. \n--------------------------------------------------------------------------\nHello Kolkata Traffic Police team,\n\nSince the time I had purchased my car in 2013, I have been monitoring your online portal for any traffic rules violation that I might have committed unintentionally for I would have to pay penalty. \n\nUp until 2015 May, there wasn\'t any pending cases against me. Checking it today, I saw that I have been subjected to a fine of Rs. 300 for over speeding on 25-Dec-2013 for which I am required to pay the aforementioned amount at Sealdah court. The case ID is M13076002. During that time I wasn\'t in Kolkata even! I was in my home town at Berhampore. Moreover, to be honest I have never ever driven around Sealdah.\n\nI would not mind paying a fine. But paying a fine for violation that I haven\'t committed sounds unfair to me. I respect your organization for the commendable job that you all do round the clock across the length and breadth of the city. Hence, I am writing my concern on your Facebook page as I firmly believe that I will get justice here. \n\nWaiting for your action and resolution.', '2017-05-10T13:23:51+0000', 'positive'),
('129115403803409_10154769004379296', 'Sir, can this case be resolved ASAP!!!!!!!\n\nI first posted this in 2015 (Refer to the write-up below). Then reposted it very recently in 2017 ( roughly 3 weeks back). I was called from for the traffic department, inquired and finally was assured that the case would get dropped as it was an incorrect tagging of the incident to my car. As a matter of fact, the case (refer to the attached snap) states to collect the license after paying the fine whereas I\'m  having my license with me all through out!!!!\n\nI till see the case to be there on your portal. \n\nMy older post on this (see below) -\n--------------------------------------------------------------------------\nHello Kolkata Traffic Police team,\n\nSince the time I had purchased my car in 2013, I have been monitoring your online portal for any traffic rules violation that I might have committed unintentionally for I would have to pay penalty. \n\nUp until 2015 May, there wasn\'t any pending cases against me. Checking it today, I saw that I have been subjected to a fine of Rs. 300 for over speeding on 25-Dec-2013 for which I am required to pay the aforementioned amount at Sealdah court. The case ID is M13076002. During that time I wasn\'t in Kolkata even! I was in my home town at Berhampore. Moreover, to be honest I have never ever driven around Sealdah.\n\nI would not mind paying a fine. But paying a fine for violation that I haven\'t committed sounds unfair to me. I respect your organization for the commendable job that you all do round the clock across the length and breadth of the city. Hence, I am writing my concern on your Facebook page as I firmly believe that I will get justice here. \n\nWaiting for your action and resolution.', '2017-05-13T06:53:56+0000', 'positive'),
('129115403803409_10154770909250246', 'Posted complain on Monday in the following website http://www.kolkatatrafficpolice.gov.in/Complaint.html but there has been no responses as of now....forgot to note the reference number as well...\n\nAuto No WB-04 / E 1963 forced me to come down at Gariahat on Monday 03/11/2014 at around 10:40 in the morning however my destination was Ballygunge. Driver said yes for Ballygunge, however at Gariahat he changed his mind and without any explanation he asked me to get down....\n\nPlease look into this....', '2014-11-05T13:14:14+0000', 'negative'),
