('129115403803409_10154785200039890', 'This car jumped red light in full speed at Ballygunge Post Office crossing. I was in a taxi and caught him at a jam in Ballygunge Phari crossing  this was at around 1.45 pm today 14th Dec.  When will these drivers learn? Lives are lost but these drivers don\'t care attitude is remarkable. This vehicle belonged to Govt of India.  Will you take any action Mr. Policemen????? I am sure you will and report it in this Facebook.', '2016-12-14T14:41:46+0000', 'negative'),
('129115403803409_10154785628219890', 'This car with a tag marked Govt of India today 14th Dec jumped the red light in full speed at Ballygunge post office at around 1.45 pm. I was in a taxi and could catch him in the traffic jam in Ballygunge Phari crossing.  I hope you will take necessary steps and please publish it on this page. We are losing precious lives everyday and want an end to it.', '2016-12-14T18:23:20+0000', 'positive'),
('129115403803409_10154797047143292', 'This car kept on driving recklessly and kept pushing other vehicles against the median while driving down to chingrighata via the salt lake stadium stretch at 8:30 am in the morning. Finally while he veered left in front of me and stopped at the chingrighata signal almost grazing my cars front bumper, i got down and confronted him to which he said its his road and he pleases to drive as he wants to as he is with the police. Does this seem like british raj once again in a well educated society. Time to feel safe again? For your kind information and needful action. \n\nLocation : chingrighata signal crossing.\nTime : 8:36 am.', '2017-04-07T03:21:52+0000', 'neutral'),
('129115403803409_10154800625348090', 'Beacon being used in the car and also saying Spl Judge?', '2017-05-15T11:20:43+0000', 'neutral'),
('129115403803409_10154806505025246', 'Yesterday (Nov 15) I saw a VIP vehicle (Honda City) parked on the road near the entrance of Quest Mall (It\'s no parking area). The vehicle number was WB02AF6529. The traffic police officers on duty tried to politely make the driver of the vehicle understand that this is a no parking zone and he should take the car inside in the parking lot. The driver totally refused and kept on making phone calls. The police gave up and the driver came out of the car when we saw two of us taking pictures of the vehicle. Someone told me its chief justice\'s car (not sure if that is true). However, if that is true, then it is a matter of great concern that the law enforcement authority\'s driver feels that the law is not for him to follow!!! Some might feel that it is a minor issue, but this is how their egos start getting bigger and bigger and soon they start feeling that they are above the law! How come no one gave him challan??? I have seen officers harass poor auto and taxi drivers. I wish they had shown some guts and snatched the fellows license and gave him a challan! But I think this is expecting too much from our police, who would do anything for so called VIPs!', '2014-11-16T14:19:48+0000', 'positive'),
