('129115403803409_10154969831361542', 'Dear Sir,\nI received this sms yesterday:\n\nWB06H3547 HAS BEEN PROSECUTED FOR Stop Line Violation, AT E M BYPASS/CANAL SOUTH ROAD/SALTLAKE BYPASS, AT 08:35 HRS VIDE CASE NO- mmPC079570/17 DATED 13-FEB-17. FOR ONLINE PAYMENT PLEASE VISIT https://kolkatatrafficpolice.net - TEAM KTP\n\nMy humble submission is that I travel daily from my home in naktala to my office at rajarhat. I am out of naktala at 8.25am daily, hence, it is impossible for me to reach the mentioned spot in 10 minutes. I would request you to kindly consider this fact and waive off my fine, if possible.\n\nI was booked for the same offense on 16th february at 8.53am, I am paying fine for that today.\n\nHoping for your kind consideration.\nBest regards', '2017-02-22T06:25:19+0000', 'positive'),
('129115403803409_10154973294294822', 'Sir,\nRight now this Van is parked near 55B Hindustan Park. My question is how a hired generator Van vehicle can use a white number plate? It so appears from its numbering sequence it is using private number plate and evading commercial tax. you may contact me at\nSamaresh Roy\nO/o pr Ag audit, west bengal,  kol-1\nMOBILE 7596815366', '2017-06-17T04:23:45+0000', 'negative'),
('129115403803409_10154991884889441', 'This is really sad and everyone on the road is in danger of this. Buses, taxis and autos rushing and racing for passengers do not care at all about others on the road. Request you the police in whom we put our faith in to really do something about this. Just imposing a fine is not good enough. A change in attitude is required of the public as a whole maybe a start could be through awareness workshops of these drivers at bus stations, auto an taxi parking points. Also request the police vehicles and cars with police stickers not to jump red traffic light (unless they are chasing a criminal) because that is another big problem so dangerous in Kolkata.', '2017-02-09T03:03:27+0000', 'positive'),
('129115403803409_10154992871679083', 'Sir nowadys there are advertisement posters on the windows of the buses. This should not be allowed keeping in mind the safety factors, windows should be completely transparent.\nOne should know how many passenger are there in the bus before stepping inside and if there is any problem going inside the bus it should be easily visible from outside. \nKindly see the attached pics for reference.', '2017-01-25T01:13:53+0000', 'negative'),
