('129115403803409_10155037857750304', 'This is what Kolkata Traffic police did to us on the road where Chai Break and Momo Plaza are located. There was no discernible No Parking sign. After a long lunch celebrating an otherwise happy occasion, our mood was instantly quelled by a brilliant show by Kolkata\'s \"Finest\".\nThey slapped illegal parking tickets on our cars even after a parking attendant helped park our cars. The mentioned attendant was nowhere to be found when we were about to leave, and were replaced by a bevy of police officers giving us tickets. The officers refused to answer any of our queries and refused to wait for the parking attendant to return. We looked for the parking attendant, who was conveniently in absentia by then. \nObviously enraged, we protested,  and the police officers, who apparently are in charge of our safety and overall wellbeing, started to play nasty. One officer screamed insults and reproves at one of us, while another officer went so far as to open his jacket, preparing to get into a physical brawl, shouting threats. \nEventually, as it always happens In India, the system won over logic and reasoning, and obvious lack of a mandatory No Parking sign. Not only did we get case tickets,  we were also the lucky recipients of an obviously errant officer catching someone by the scruff of his neck and another one of us (a girl,  no less) roughly on the arm, vowing to \"leave you with a scar\".\n\n\nThis lane is a popular hangout zone for the young generation and we urge anyone else who faced what we did today to share their experiences.  This is the only way to create awareness and let people know that the so-called law enforcement officials are being consumed by corruption and greed, a little more everyday.\nWe don\'t know what exactly is going on, but it seems ridiculous that a parking attendant is assisting a whole line of cars to park, and conveniently disappears suddenly,  only to be replaced by an army of \"righteous\" police officers.', '2015-01-10T12:01:52+0000', 'positive'),
('129115403803409_10155060200373524', '2/3/2017, 8:40 AM, Lords More. Do the rules regarding STOP line apply differently for that guy in white on the red motorbike because he\'s a cop? Eventually he crossed over while the signal was still red. It reminded me of Pankaj Roy, the famous cricketer, who used to say - \"lawmakers should not be lawbreakers.\"', '2017-03-02T04:38:05+0000', 'positive'),
