('129115403803409_10155144200444019', 'Dear Authorities,\nToday on the B.T. Road near Talla bridge, at 2200 hrs, this truck wrongly collided with our vehicle I20, and drove our car more than half a mile while in collision! The driver was completely drunk and was not in a position to even stand!We were shocked to see that there was not a single traffic police who was available then at that point till Shyambazar crossing! We stopped the truck and wanted to take the culprit, the driver to Police Station but could not do so as he almost drove his truck over me! Neither the police nor the onlookers gave a helping hand to put the culprit to the task! \nI am really pained to see that not a single traffic police was posted there and even if they were posted, they were not around or even came forward to help!!! What are the parameters of accident? I could have died with my daughter if we wouldn\'t have reacted in the right way! Do you people consider someone a culprit only if they run over someone or kill innocent people! Really pained  and feeling agitated seeing the condition of our city! Need justice! Want that drunk driver put behind the bars so that he is not left loose to kill someone else\'s life!!!', '2017-04-20T17:57:29+0000', 'negative'),
('129115403803409_10155149749171318', 'The traffic police on duty made my wife make the turn during a red light to ease traffic. Please check surveillance and revert. \nWB06C9843 HAS BEEN PROSECUTED FOR Stop Line Violation, AT A J C BOSE ROAD (SOUTH)/SHAKESPEARE SARANI/P, AT 07:47 HRS VIDE CASE NO- crPC130251/17 DATED 02-MAR-17. FOR ONLINE PAYMENT PLEASE VISIT https://kolkatatrafficpolice.net - TEAM KTP', '2017-03-04T03:49:00+0000', 'negative'),
('129115403803409_10155154267429387', 'This car carrying a WB govt officer hit our car on our left rear side causing substantial damage. The reckless driver was about to hit another car as well. Upon confronting, the driver kept arguing while the officer sitting behind and busy talking on his phone, didn\'t even bother to look up. I kept asking him that if he takes any moral responsibility for this to which he asked his driver to just move on! \n\nThere was Kolkata traffic police signal there. I asked the traffic police on duty to stop the car and take appropriate action. They asked the driver to stop. The driver didn\'t obey and just drove off! \n\nSo, are all the rules and laws of the land only for ordinary citizens like us? Can a Govt vehicle carrying Govt official just get away breaking all traffic rules? \n\nProbably, this arrogance has come from repeatedly taking advantage of the system and never having to be accountable for it. \n\nWill Kolkata Police do anything in this regard and help us restore our faith in the system?\n\nThe incident took place at the Dhalai Bridge crossing beside Khudiram Metro Station.', '2017-09-15T05:22:20+0000', 'positive'),
