('129115403803409_10155277460375457', 'This is the second time I am lodging a complaint about the taxi stand next to Ashabari building complex in Baishnabghata Patuli Township. Today, 21 February 2015, at 10:05am there were at least 8 taxis at the stand with all their drivers and the two starters present and no one was willing to go to Gariahat. When i was taking down their numbers I was threatened that no cab would ever be given to me from there and when I caught a running cab they were threatening the driver of that taxi and asking him to not stop. I would of course like thank the government for bringing down the fine from 3000/- to 100/- for refusal. It has been of great service to the commuters.\n I would like to lodge a formal complaint where I am given a complaint no. with which I can check up on the status of complaint from time to time. The complaint is against the starter as well as the individual taxi drivers. The numbers of the cars that I could take down are as follows : \nWB04 D8843; WB04 G1780; WB04 G0820; WB19 B1134; WB04 B6695\n\nMy phone number is +91 9830016045', '2015-02-21T07:11:27+0000', 'negative'),
