('129115403803409_10155296323764669', 'I would like to bring to your notice the rampant parking on the wrong side of the road which occurs every Sunday on Lee Road. I have aytached a photo taken this evening. There is a \"parking attendant\" who collects rs.20/- per hour from each car. This causes huge traffic jams and severely inconveniences residents like us, who find it difficult to access our homes. I would greatly appreciate prompt action on your part. I honestly believe the Kolkata Traffic Police do a stellar job to keep the traffic moving in this city. Kudos to you!!', '2017-04-23T12:56:07+0000', 'negative'),
('129115403803409_10155314069593540', 'On 7th May 2017 me and my family had a near fatal experience due to negligent and rash driving by the driver of ambassador car number WB 02Y 9884- Avijit Chakraborty of Panihati. We were driving at a slow pace in Rajarhat Eco Urban Village area and were at a crossing when we saw the ambassador speeding at break neck speed towards our vehicle from the left side road. The road was virtually empty except for our vehicles and the driver was extremely negligent and absent minded, as he dashed towards us and in all possibility missed slowing down and failed to apply brakes resulting in dashing into my almost new Honda Mobilio Car. \n\nIf it was not the car I would not have been writing this now. The man was extremely inconsiderate and was attempting to run off and did not even come to assist us with medical aid. We were given assistance by unknown passerby\'s. My baby girl of 1 year, my mother aged 75 years, my husband and myself were injured in the accident with cuts, bruises and sprains, the pain of which still exists. My son and our ayah escaped unhurt I was not in a physical/ mental state to put in this complaint before. I request strong action to be taken against this in sensitive, irresponsible rash driver at the earliest. The driver who had promised at the Police Station to pay a part of the damages is refusing to do so now. A GD has been lodged by my husband on this case at New Town Police Station, Kolkata. Attaching pic for reference.', '2017-05-19T11:16:42+0000', 'negative'),
