('129115403803409_10155618374234803', 'Biker without helmet coming from wrong side. Topsia, near Porsche showroom~3pm 16 August. No, I don\'t have his number so please don\'t ask. KTP doesn\'t have enough staff to man these crossings but there are enough people to take imaginary numbers for issuing false citations. So thugs and ruffians can flagrantly flout the law, we all know why, while honest people are continuously armtwisted.', '2017-08-16T15:29:38+0000', 'neutral'),
('129115403803409_10155619893479803', 'I saw in a post that KTP has asked a gentleman to provide any documents that he may have to prove he wasn\'t at the point where he was prosecuted. A basic principle that applies in such a case is that one cannot prove a negative. Also the burden of proving a violation lies with the police, and one is innocent till proven guilty, not the other way round. Since I don\'t travel much, I thought of a rough method which other fellow citizens may want to try.  This is the picture of the odometer of my car at 7.59 am 17 August, 2017. It reads 5421 km. Since FB permits only one picture to be posted at a time, I will post another as comment.', '2017-08-17T03:52:20+0000', 'positive'),
('129115403803409_10155631269236178', 'Yesterday I parked my Santro Car at Madan Street  (Chandni) so when the parking guy asked me for money as per KMC rule i given him Rs.10 then he said sir its Rs.20 so i thought may be the parking fee vary from place to place and paid him that...\nWhen i reached my office then only i realised that he tagged my car in bus category and charged me extra.\n\nPlease look into this matter.', '2017-06-18T05:28:34+0000', 'positive'),
('129115403803409_10155669543885628', 'Traffic position at Rabindra Sarani near nakhuda mosque. Illegal parking, double line parking unloading in the middle of the rod. No Seargent, no home guard. No order no discipline.', '2017-05-17T06:44:10+0000', 'neutral'),
('129115403803409_10155674606991639', 'I write on behalf of the poor Uber driver who got challaned for overspending, whilst driving @50 km/hr as clocked by you, stating that the speed limit was a mere 30km/hr on a 50 ft wide one-way thoroughfare namely CR Avenue.\nCan you please explain the logics behind this speed limit. \nOn the one hand KMC is broadening the roads, and on the other hand you are reducing the speed limits to pathetic values. \nA cycle today can touch 30km/hr. \nCars change to third gear after attaining 30km/hr. Does it mean that cars should now be driven on only 1st & 2nd gears.\nWouldn\'t this reduce their mileage drastically apart from causing jams as everyone would be driving at a snails space.\nPlease immediately change this pathetic illogical speed limits and oblige the citizens of calcutta. \nYou have made a 7km expressway and here also kept limits ranging btwn 30 and 60 km. \nPlease, we aren\'t driving bullock carts in this century.', '2017-09-07T07:32:10+0000', 'negative'),
('129115403803409_10155739548696562', 'We were on our way to my wife\'s office at Ultadanga from Ruby General Hospital while we were stuck in a traffic at around 9:40a.m near the Uttar Panchanna GRAM signal, where the broad road tapers over the canal near the signal. It is a usual scene everyday where the buses try to overtake each other from the left and then speed up where the road gets narrow blocking the cars moving in the straight path. We were standing in the traffic waiting for the green signal to light up, when a CSTC bus numbered WB-04E 0440 hurriedly rushed forward from behind  and started brushing our car in the left side where my wife was sitting. Usually a car / bus stops at the sound of a contact with another car or with a jerk, but it deliberately kept on moving tearing and damaging the left side of the car; infact the damage deepened while it moved ahead, which means it was moving to the right totally ignorant of the fact that the driver\'s action could actually have killed someone. When we went out of the car to resolve the issue, the adamant bus driver was extremely rude not only to me but to my wife too, telling her in Bengali that \'he would have only cared to resolve the issue only if someone had died on the spot\'. My wife is still in a state of shock after the incident and we would like you to take strict actions against the ignorant driver of the bus numbered WB-04 E 0440 as it could have easily turned into something horrifying and deadly.\n\nDATE OF INCIDENT : 20/01/2017\nTIME: AROUND 9:40 AM TO 9:50 AM\nPLACE: NEAR UTTAR PANCHANNA GRAM CROSSING', '2017-01-20T08:53:59+0000', 'negative'),
('129115403803409_10155749387053249', 'This cab asked for 350 Rs. without meter from Lenin Sarani to Newtown. When I told that I will go by meter and will pay as per meter (even it is more) , he refused. It happened at around 1 pm yesterday e.g. Oct 05, 2017', '2017-10-05T18:51:55+0000', 'neutral'),
('129115403803409_10155770791815492', 'This picture is taken at the crossing near ESI Hospital, Maniktala. Vehicles moving from Kankurgachi towards Ultadanga and turning right to take the road beside ESI Hospital onto EM Bypass often have confusion on the right turn traffic signal. I daily take this route and always have difficulty in knowing when to turn right. The traffic signal on the top left of the picture is very difficult to see and one cannot see clearly the right turn signal. \nThere is a traffic signal setup on the right side (marked in the picure) which is before the crossing and this does not have the right turn signal. So, often cars are not able to see the signal and don\'t know when to turn. \n\nCan I please suggest a traffic signal be installed right after the crossing in the centre (marked in the picture below) with the straight and right turn signals ? This route is busy almost throughout the day and it would be great if a proper signal which is able to be seen clearly is installed to avoid difficulty in driving.', '2015-06-14T15:44:07+0000', 'negative'),
('129115403803409_10155779296546521', 'This auto rikshaye was rash driving at 6.35 pm 21.2.2017. When confronted the driver was cursing and threatening that they will do grievous bodily injury to my driver. I hope kolkata police will take steps to control this arrogant auto driver', '2017-02-21T13:08:25+0000', 'neutral'),
('129115403803409_10155796283345131', 'Jumping a red light at Chowringhee. How do you expect the common public to abide by the law when the law maker turns into a law breaker.', '2015-03-31T05:29:40+0000', 'positive'),
('129115403803409_10155880282330931', 'On 3rd june 2017, we were on the paikpara crossing at around 11pm in our maruti suzuki swift desire vehicle number wb24aj 9339 when suddenly an ola cab hitted us from behind.\n\nHis vehicle number is Wb 15b 8456\nWhite Indica.\n\nM also sending you my damaged car pics with this message.\n\nPls act soon against that rouge driver and kindly confirm.\n\nThanks in advance.', '2017-06-04T15:25:11+0000', 'positive'),
('129115403803409_10155980040193872', 'Whenever I tried to catch a Taxi, Taxi walas seems to make mockery of No Refusal rule. It\'s just a normal things on the roads of kolkata that passengers are just left helpless.  This time (around 6.30 PM)I tried to hail a Taxi from Ramkrishna Seva Pratisthan and one after another Taxi were refusing to go to Kankurganchi. Than I saw two Taxis standing on the road. I approached both of them and both refused to go meanwhile one left the spot. When I asked second one why you are not going he replied that\'s not my area. Than I asked from which date govt gave you area permit. He just bluntly said he will not go.  I ask him  than why you are car is on the road go to garage. Than came a local goon in-between he ordered him(to taxi driver) not to go anywhere let me see what anybody can do to you. I was surprised and shocked not on breaking of law but audacity of these people. Please register case against errant taxi for refusal and misbehavior.', '2017-12-02T15:28:48+0000', 'negative'),
('129115403803409_1015603445185033', 'So many accidents due to negligence which causes death in Port area. \nThere are so many such cases we witnessed were container toppled on pedestrian and other small vehicle causing spot deaths. \nIn picture you can see the container is not properly locked. \nWe demand strong action against these negligence', '2016-03-18T14:37:37+0000', 'positive'),
