('129115403803409_10156727794743448', 'Hi team, \n\nLocation: hudco crossing, ultadanga\nAffected vehicle: Hyundai xcent WB12D3541\n\nI was standing in hudco crossing around 5-7mins back due to red signal and an auto came from behind and put up a stunt which caused a large scratch at the back of my car. The car was not even moving that another vehicle can hit it on the move, it was simply standing at the signal. The auto driver kept on bragging how he wanted to go to the other side and the colour will go off my car if I use break oil to remove it and how it is so normal to get a scratch if u r on road. The most upsetting part is there were no traffic guard around to complaint during the whole conversation with the auto driver for about 10 minutes. I had to move my vehicle as I was going to office and was in a rush. Please look into this.', '2017-11-06T04:24:00+0000', 'negative'),
