('129115403803409_10158641614425545', 'Hi, my car no WB06G2811 has been prosecuted vide case no crPC244825/17 dated 22-05-2017 at 09:48 AM for stop line violation.\n\nLet me bring to your notice, this image has been shared by you is very accurate as I was at the wheel today and my father was seated next to me. However, this is an incomplete story.\n\nLike everyday we were crossing this signal and very clearly we crossed the signal when it was green and we went quiet further ahead. The silver amaze car that you can see in the photo was even ahead of me when the light changed to yellow.\n\nAs the light changed to yellow, we saw a handful of cars not stopping, choosing to risk their lives and going ahead. We however chose to stop and decided to reverse our car.\n\nAfter we reversed, we patiently waited for the signal to turn green. It is at this time that this picture has been taken and my car has been prosecuted for stop line violation. In reality we crossed when it was green. \n\nWhile I was waiting, I also identified the camera which would capture this image and we were pretty sure we would receive this case. Now please do not send me a message stating that after thorough investigation you feel the prosecution is justified. This time it is not justified. Kindly rectify the same.\n\nYour urgent attention on this matter would be highly solicited.\n\nBest Regards,\n\nA Law abiding and rule following citizen,\nPrateek', '2017-05-22T10:07:25+0000', 'neutral'),
('129115403803409_10158651285100232', 'This is the Brabourne road flyover as we exit Ns road, every evening shuttle cars to howrah are parked in the opposite direction in a highly congested crossing, kolkata traffice police is well aware of the situation and we call traffic control every evening reporting the same problem yet this continues, you and me even if we cross the stop line there is fine but as usual ktp shuts its eyes where nuisance is committed on a daily basis..if this is not a collusion of politicians - police and the operators then what is????', '2017-04-19T04:48:38+0000', 'negative'),
