('129115403803409_10200443905656487', 'My Maruti Swift Dzire (WB 06H 5286)  was enroute from Anandapur towards Kasba at around 4.10 pm on 04th May 2015, when at the Ruby Crossing a Delhi Public School Bus, WB 19A 4527, rapidly tried to overtake us bruising my entire car from the driver\'s side and shattering the tail lamp of my car into pieces. We tried to confront the driver, but even after our complaints he refused to apologize or accept his mistake and rushed away from the scene. I could not contact any police officer during that time due to any personal emergency hence I want to post the complaint here. This is a very important issue because School Drivers who are supposed to be entrusted with the lives of 100s of students are now engaged in such rough and irresponsible driving. I would request you to please look into this matter and take any action against the driver and the school if needed so that incidents like this do not happen in the future.', '2015-05-04T12:50:47+0000', 'negative'),
('129115403803409_10200789341333716', 'Would like to draw your attention to the incident that my husband encountered while driving down EM ByPass today in his ZEN Estillo bearing No WB06J 0789 around 2 pm this afternoon near Uttar Panchanna Gram to be precise. While he was waiting at the traffic signal a Maruti Alto car bearing No WB16AK 7805 rammed into his stationary car at a great speed. The suddenness of the incident caused him a neck sprain and damaged the car. Thankfully he was saved from any physical injury. The police sergeant attending to his duties nearby arrived at the scene immediately but strangely was of the opinion that such an issue be sorted between the reckless driver and the victim , in this case my husband.He did not even ask for the licence of the reckless driver leave alone impose any fine or impound his licence. The errant driver fleed the spot and my husband proceeded to lodge a complaint with Tiljala PS and put the damaged car into the workshop.\nMy concerns are\n1. When traffic policemen slap fines for even very minor lapses on the part of drivers how could a reckless driver causing considerable damage to a vehicle be just let off?\n2. Why was the driver not even asked to show his licence? What if he is not even eligible to drive.\n3. Why do we always have to wait for something fatal to happen until we take a step against rash drivers who ram into a stationary vehicle?\n4. When violating a signal, parking on the road (even when a No parking sign is absent) are treated as offences, on what grounds are reckless drivers let off?\nJust to add the police officials at Tiljala PS have been very cordial and helpful according to my husband but I as a wife, mother and a woman who drives her own car would request Kolkata Traffic Police to be much more proactive in their role in booking drivers who cause accidents which can no way be ignored as minor mistakes. The passive role of the traffic sergeant in this case added as a boost for the errant driver who might cause many more such casualties and who knows one might just turn fatal.\nAttaching herewith the pic of the car which caused damage to my husband\'s car(obviously the front portion of the car got damaged too).\nPlease do give us some hope.', '2015-08-20T17:54:41+0000', 'negative'),
