('129115403803409_10203078675888403', 'A taxi which me and my mother caught today near Bhowanipore PS refused to deviate from Ashutosh Mukherjee Rd and proceed to another smaller road (Dr. Rajendra Road) saying that we had not informed him about that and refused to let us out of the vehicle.He finally let us out of the vehicle after charging 40Rupees.\n\nA video of the incident: http://goo.gl/ytzwUp .\nA private message has been sent to the Kolkata Police page wherein further details and contact info has been disclosed.', '2015-07-02T12:21:31+0000', 'neutral'),
('129115403803409_10203100871261469', 'The most disciplined mode of transport are trams. They stick to their lanes, do not overtake, do not over speed, wait for their turn very patiently. It is the very nature of trams cause they stick to their tram lines (lanes) and have no other choice.\n\nAll other, motor driven modes are unruly and block the trams.\n\nAs traffic police you should *enforce* discipline on the cars, autos, taxis and buses rather than penalize trams.\n\nAll over the world, trams are allowed the first right of way over the other modes of transport.\n\nWorst possible thought that has come from your department. For your inability to manage and enforce traffic rules, you are blaming trams which are most disciplined.\n\nThe referred senior officer in this article below from Times of India, needs a bit of education about the benefits of trams over cars, buses and taxis.\n\n', '2014-06-05T02:46:37+0000', 'negative'),
