('129115403803409_10204134786145293', 'GUYS please read THIS... THis is how THE KOLKATA POLICE LOOTS US AND GO AROUND WITH ILL BEHAVIOUR.\n\nThis is to bring to your notice that the Kolkata traffic police had harassed and used abusive language. \nThe incident took place  near Jaggubazar where i had gone with my friend . My car was parked behind a car that was already parked usually the stretch where cars are parked on sunday ! I had parked it on sunday for my 10 minutes work at jaggubazar. \nWhen i came back i saw the clamp on my tyre .\nI was astonished to know the stretch where my car was parked was a no parking zone and having known that i went upto the cop sitting inside the crane standing next to our car. I and another man whose car was clamped  requested for spot fine. The COP agreed to it and charged a sum of Rs 300/- (Rs 100 for Kolkata police , Govt of West Bengal Dept fund challan No 350973and Rs 200 for challan in the name of Saini crane lifters challan number 3899 ) \nAfter paying there i saw there were 2 cars with Govt of West Bengal stickers also parked in the NO parking zone same as mine . \nI asked the cop to charge those cars with fine as well and i stood there to assure it happens. When i informed the cop that i am waiting to that he replied \" wait korun aami das ghanta aachi\". To which i had to reply \"aami oo aachi\" .\nAfter the other man\'s fine was taken i now asked the police cop very politely \" Please could u fine the two cars too i am waiting\" after hearing this the cop asked his driver to start the crane and leave. \nI told him this is injustice and you please fine them as they are parked in no parking too as my cars to which he says \"president hobe to aami president ke fine debo na\" and the crane started moving ahead . I demanded to know his name and took his photograph . As he knew he was wrong he got abusive  to my female friend who was also trying to click the picture and said \" F*** Off\" . I still do not believe that this is the behaviour of Kolkata police and how could he use foul language? As a well educated citizen of this country and a respected resident in Kolkata i think THIS partial behaviour and to add foul language is simply not acceptable . This is harassmeent in real sense and a car with govt of india sticker should also be charged with the same fine and such a abusive and rowdy behaviour by a officer on duty is not acceptable.\n \nCop NAME : Mr. S.PAL ( additional officer in charge - Bhawanipur traffic guard )\nplease find the pics of the cop the copy of the challans are also there with me , but your page allows only a single pic to be uploaded so i have uploaded the cops for your reference.', '2014-09-17T08:05:55+0000', 'positive'),
