('129115403803409_10205850427160125', 'A query for the KTP Leadership : Could the colour coding related to traffic congestion on roads, found on Google Maps( Traffic section ), be considered by citizens on wheels in selecting the less congested routes to their destinations?  \n\nIf yes then KTP should also encourage and advise citizens in using the same.\n\nGeneral concept :\n\nRed- Heavy congestion. \n\nOrange - Moderate congestion \n\nGreen - Smooth passage. \n\nPlease clarify.', '2016-02-06T05:34:55+0000', 'positive'),
('129115403803409_10205896815280346', 'Today, 21/01/2016 at 07:45pm I stopped my car outside Cakes, near Loudon street where this traffic guard(in blue uniform) came and told me that you can\'t park the car here so I started to take left as there was the parking line but as there was huge traffic I couldn\'t cross, still i was trying, I didn\'t just park the car there. Suddenly the guard came in front of my car and wrote my car\'s number. So is this what traffic police is all about? Without any specific reason writing down the number as the traffic guards have the right to do anything? We as the citizens are always wrong and police is always right? No. \nThis thing didn\'t stopped there. I thought of taking action against that guard. I went to Shakespeare Sarani Police station, I told everything there and they started telling me that you have to write a letter, have to send it to Lal bazar police station, one letter you have to submit here. My question to them was can\'t they take an action now, on the spot? They could have called that police guard in the police station and they could have asked him in front of me what happened there, but they were busy talking, actually gossiping with each other. It felt like No one cares what is happening outside. So at last one sergeant gave me an e-mail id and told me to mail the letter as nothing can be done now. \nAs a result, Nothing happened on the spot. I didn\'t got any help from the police station. Nor that guard had any shame as he was laughing with other sergeants outside the police station. So that proud traffic guard Mr. Somnath Kundu is laughing and this is what happened today with me will be continuing till we have these kinds of traffic guards. \nWriting a post here means I want the #KolkataTrafficPoliceDepartment  to take an action to this soon because I can\'t wait for a case letter to be sent at my address for that thing which I haven\'t done.', '2016-01-21T19:08:15+0000', 'negative'),
