('129115403803409_10206292516015635', 'Picture of our car, damaged by a reckless driver.\nDuring your so-called Road Safety Week!!\nOur car was standing at a red light. Another car, Reg no. WB 06G 0830 driven by one Dinesh Paswan, hit it from the left and took off the fender, and tried to speed away, breaking the red light!!\nHe was stopped by other motorists. My wife, who was present, lodged an MCR. Regent Park P.S MCR No 22 dt 05.02.15 against the vehicle/driver as dictated by th Officer, S.I. R.G.P [Ms] Chakrabaorty.\nI paid 5700.00 for the repairs. \nThe driver was allowed to drive off with his license, scot free!\nSo much for your farcical Road Traffic Safety Week!\nJust who are you fooling?', '2015-02-16T14:56:37+0000', 'neutral'),
('129115403803409_10206298055393223', 'This taxi parked near Jadavpur University Gate 2 would not go to Ballygunge Phari, Broad Street at 10:45 am today, because he didn\'t feel so. The guy very blatantly said he does not care if I call the police, or report. So I am just trying my luck..', '2015-03-22T05:29:48+0000', 'positive'),
('129115403803409_10206403654586886', 'Equality before law and equal protection of law has now become just a theory in books only we all know. As the traffic rules, not wearing a helmet during riding a bike is a \"punishable offence\", but only for common people it seems...The authorities whose job is to see that people are abiding by the laws sadly are the the ones breaking it for their convenience. This policeman [ as we can see KP (Kolkata police) marked on his bike] was riding a bike with a lady who was not wearing a helmet..and other policemen just stood and saw silently.And it is not an offence for them because he is a policeman. If we the common people would have been in his place,we would have been fined as law states. Why the rules and laws are not applicable to them? They are public servants and if they break such laws ,the punishment should be severe. If they don\'t abide by the laws of our land,how can we expect the common people to abide by the laws? We expect that a severe legal action should be taken against those public servants who are the bad examples of our society.', '2015-05-31T19:44:50+0000', 'positive'),
