('129115403803409_10206669340212115', 'A wrong case was registered against my vehicle on 18.03.2017.As per the CCTV footage,it is clearly visible that by oversight Kolkata Traffic Police has registered the case.I have sent a mail with the CCTV footage to Kolkata Traffic Police on 24.03.2017 to withdraw the case.Till date neither I have received any feedback nor the case has been withdrawn.I am enclosing the mail & also uploading the CCTV image here.Hope to get a response soon now.\n\nFrom: Jay Pramanik <jaypramanik@gmail.com>\nDate: Fri, 24 Mar 2017 17:38:52 +0530\nSubject: Wrong Case for traffic violation for WB02AE 3236\nTo: dctp@kolkatatrafficpolice.gov.in\nCc: dctraffickol@gmail.com\n\nDear Sir,\n\nThis is for your kind information,that I own a White Coloured Maruti Ertiga with Registration Number-WB02AE 3236.On 18th March\'17 I received a SMS from Kolkata Traffic Police that my car has been prosecuted for Stop Line Violation at E M ByPass/Bagmari Road (N)/P at 10:20 hrs Vide Case No-crPC145841/17 dated 18.03.2017 I was surprised to receive this SMS,as I didn\'t travel by that road at 10:20 hrs.Today again I have received a reminder SMS from Kolkata Traffic Police to pay the fine.\n\nWhen i searched for the details regarding this case in the payments page,the image which was uploaded,clearly showed,that the stop line violation was done by a blue coloured hyundai,with a number plate of 3238,but it looks like 3236 from a distance.The person in your department,who is responsible for booking cases,by going through the CCTV images,should have been more careful.I am enclosing the uploaded image for your reference.\n\nPlease withdraw the case against my car & oblige.\n\nThanks,\n\nRegards,\nJay Pramanik', '2017-04-07T06:20:00+0000', 'negative'),
