('129115403803409_10208488782713227', 'Good-day Sirs ,\n\nWRT stop line violations request kindly advise flwg : \n\n1. How many seconds the amber light blinks  before light turns from green to red . The reason I am enquiring same is that I reside in the Kasba/Ruby connector (at Bose pukur) and I feel unnecessary victimised as the light suddenly turns from green to red with the amber light blinking for half second in between . \nLast 2 months I hv received 2 challans for stop line violation when my car stopped maybe ahead of the stop line bcos the light suddenly turned from green to red.\nIn one instance it was at the bosepukur sitala Mandir crossing when my car had just taken fuel from the pump and was coming out .. there was no momentum . \n\nWhen I went to enquire with the constable handling the signal at  sitala mandir crossing he said that the light duration is in auto mode and fixed by lalbazar. They cannot do anything about it . \n\n2. The stop lines are drawn far off from the crossing sometimes as much as 10-15 mtrs from the crossing . Classic example is the stop line drawn at Siemens crossing for traffic flowing towards Ruby (10-15 mtrs) from the Siemens crossing . In this case what will we do if we cross the stop sign and light turns red . If car stops u give stop line violation . I car speeds away you give crossing signal in red light violation . \n\nWould request your kind comments in this matter . Also is it possible to gv the amber light blinking for 3 seconds prior turning red . \n\nMy 2 case numbers as follows :\n\n1. CASE NO- vvPC073309/17 DATED 03-MAR-17. \n2.CASE NO- vvPC070902/17 DATED 21-FEB-17.', '2017-03-29T05:33:13+0000', 'positive'),
