('129115403803409_10210327573398572', 'Today while I was passing by Gurusaday Road at 5:35PM, my car was stopped by a police sergeant subordinate, who accused me of breaking traffic rules. On being asked what rule I had broken, he said that he saw me crossing the signal from the other side of the road. I responded saying that this is a normal practice, when the traffic light is green many other vehicles also follow the same route, a video of the same has been uploaded as a proof. Also there was no sign board prohibiting the same.\nEven if that would have been an offence, as per the common place traffic rules, only a spot fine of Rs.100 can be taken from the violater, but the sergeant name Mr. Bijoy Kumar Paul has forcefully taken my driver\'s licence. Not only this, his utter disregard for being just clearly shows in the video; when I asked why only I am being caught if it is an offence, & not the other cars following me. Then on numerous later rounds of the signal, there was a bureaucrat car with a blue light & several red light cars, who took the same route. On asking why those cars were not penalised, he responded saying that it was an emergency car. I was shocked at the height of discrimination, as we all clearly know that only ambulances, fire brigades,etc. are considered emergency vehicles. Also, I was told that only the first car will be penalised & not others. Secondly, he also oversmartly instrcted his subordinates not to allow cars to follow the same route so that i cant capture it in the video, but he couldnt succeed as it is a common practice followed by all on Gurusaday road. \nWhen I was not around, he forcefully pressurised my poor driver for his licence, which was his only ID proof available with him as he was going to travel to his village the next day. He begged to pay a spot fine in lieu of the licence, as he had no option. But being arrogant, egoistic, & rude, the sergeant did his unjust decision.\nIs this the injustice that the Kolkata traffic policemen are doing to harrass commoners by taking away their licence or charging fine only to the first offender? This shows that it is a practice of pocket filling by the policemen, who scare common people & take undue advantage from them, to falsely show their efficiency to their seniors. Saying \" JO KARNA HAI KARIYE COURT ME JAA KE\" why am I being sent to the court without any reason!! \n\nKolkata Traffic Police', '2017-04-13T15:04:11+0000', 'positive'),
