('129115403803409_10212205520110823', 'This is the 4th time I am raising this concern.\nOut of all 9 cases 5 cases are near La Martiniere School; Rawdon Street.\nFor 3 marked in yellow I already raised in this page and it was said your concern is sent to concerned department.\nQuery is once sent to concerned department, I did not receive any feedback.\nNow, when I am checking I see that nothing has been done in this regard.\nDoes this statement really means anything, or this is just a false commitment?? A BIG LIE.\nComing to the sections charged, in this 122/177 MVA - \'Improper and Obstructive Parking\' is given - first of all no parking is allowed on Rawdon street near La Martiniere School. But one has to get down and get up in the car with a kid with him/her. In this case its my mother who is an elderly lady. If 30 seconds of such time is said to be penalised under this section then I probably would call for a clarification for the same.\nNext section charged is 119/177 MVA - \'Red Light Jumping\' then where on earth is Red Signal near La Martiniere school. If you mean to say AJC Bose Road to La Martiniere School then you must be knowing a single cycle cannot pass in Red Signal as always 2 to 3 traffic guards are there ALWAYS. Same is case from Rawdon Street to Shakespeare Sarani crossing.\nI am attaching mail to \'esttp.guard@kolkatatrafficpolice.gov.in\', \'dctp@kolkatatrafficpolice.gov.in, dctraffickol@gmail.com, dctp@kolkatapolice.gov.in\' sent in this regard in the comment.\nBut no email has been received or an acknowledgement as courtesy.\nPlease let me know do I need to pay for these false cited offences at Rawdon Street or I receive a confirmation of dismissal of these offences.\nRest I will pay as really I could not recollect and probably they are true.\nCan I get an answer please?', '2017-03-20T17:23:10+0000', 'positive'),
