('129115403803409_10213395494548269', 'Understanding the traffic signals:\n1. We all know the RED light means you stop. YELLOW means caution, O sorry, its no longer caution, it\'s STOP. While rest of the world is caution for yellow, its STOP in Kolkata. Motorist are given no time to check the movement of vehicle and are being penalized for jumping signal. Previously the timers helped the motorist in judging the time and act accordingly, but now most of the crossing timers are shown for waiting period only, and not when to stop. Also yellow blinkers do not function, and switches to RED immediately. This is resulting in crossing STOP LINE and stop on zebra crossing. Any solution for this from KTP?\n2. While driving behind a bus or lorry, its difficult for smaller car to view traffic signals. Many times, the bus crosses and the car behind has to either stop crossing the stop line, or get a ticket for jumping signal. Can you suggest how to overcome this?', '2017-04-25T07:21:02+0000', 'neutral'),
