('129115403803409_1098810666839688', 'Taxi Refusal :\n\nAround 4.35pm on Brabourne Road (left flank) i asked this cab driver to take me to Bowbazar. The driver agreed and i was about to get into the cab. But immediately another group of 4-5 persons started boarding the cab i was surprised to see that after trying for so long i found a cab who was ready to pick me but these people so easily got into the cab and were unwilling to get down. They started arguing with the driver to which i asked him to take the cab left side and seek for police help. Inspite of his requests the group was adamant and didn\'t leave the cab. \nI asked the driver to straight away tell them to get down since i had convinced him first. But he failed. They didn\'t listen a word and so did the driver. \nUnfortunately the cab driver took them instead of me and i had to again struggle for another cab which i found almost an hour later. \nIt can be understood that during the festival days it\'s difficult finding a cab, but finding a cab and then letting it go to such stubborn people is tough to accept.\nThe driver could have easily got them off his vehicle provided he could have called for police help. He too wasn\'t interested in taking them for a ride but it seemed they were forcing him beyond the limit. \nHoping the cab driver doesn\'t let this happen to anyone else ever again.', '2016-10-28T11:57:32+0000', 'negative'),
