('129115403803409_1149620131820155', 'Till date neither I received resolution for FB Memo NO-645 nor the same has been resolved.\n\nI am giving KTP 3 more days to resolve the issue failing which I will file RTI against KTP asking evidence as well as I will lodge a Case in Consumer court regarding the same.\nKindly treat this as urgent and do let me know your input within the stipulated timeline.\n\nEarlier communication is stated below with KTP\'s reply:\n\nI made a post in this page on October 18 at 11:41am stating the following..\nToday morning I received a message:\nWB02AE0880 HAS BEEN PROSECUTED FOR Light Signal Violation, AT RUBI ISLAND, AT 15:02 HRS VIDE CASE NO- vvPC047852/16 DATED 13-OCT-16. FOR ONLINE PAYMENT PLEASE VISIT https://kolkatatrafficpolice.net - TEAM KTP\n\nBut, I didn\'t went to Ruby or South Kolkata that day.\nI stay in Rajarhat and I was in office the whole day in Sec V, Salt Lake. My car was parked in my office parking.\nThere must be a mistake by the system. Tell me what needs to be done from my side to prove this is wrong!!\nSwarup Saha\n\nReply received from Kolkata Traffic Police:\n\nThanks for the post. We are checking it up. Kindly share your contact no. for any future interaction, if required. Regards.\n\nBut as of now neither anybody contacted me nor the case been withdrawn.\nKolkata Traffic Police Any update on this? Can you show me the evidence that my car violated any signal on that day? Or else let me know how can I file complain against your system. Hope I will get justice.\nRemember: This is a matter of Rs 100/- which I can easily pay. But still want to fight against this.\n\nAgain I received the reply from KTP which are as below:\n\nKolkata Traffic Police:\nThanks for your post. We will back to you very soon with feedback. Please bear with us. Regards.\nOctober 31 at 4:32pm\n\nKolkata Traffic Police: \nYour case is under investigation. You will be notified through a Facebook post vide FB Memo NO-645. Pl. bear with us. Regards.\n\nNovember 1 at 2:59pm', '2016-12-08T15:00:10+0000', 'neutral'),
