('129115403803409_1151199784935100', 'Dear sir,\n I have received a message for stop line violation at shyambazar 5 point crossing (north)at 6.16 pm today. This is completely unnecessary, unacceptable and unethical from my perspective and amounts to harrasment. \nI was in the car when my driver crossed the stop signal at the aforementioned point but the speed was pretty slow owing to vehicles infront of mine and by the time my car reached the crossing, the signal turned yellow and my driver immediately stopped the car. I was in the extreme right lane and my car was the first vehicle. I was talking over the phone in the backseat with my wife and got annoyed that we had to stop because of the vehicles (buses) infront. One policeman in white uniform and wearing helmet had also raised his hand just at that point to stop the traffic. So we had just abided by the law and not broken any rule. This is a harrassment. I refuse to pay for it. Please see the footage from cctv of that period.\nN.B. a copy of the message received is given below.\n Regards.\nSomdeb Mitra\nAssistant Professor\nUniversity of Calcutta\n\nCopy of the message:\n\nWB02AF7738 HAS BEEN PROSECUTED FOR Stop Line Violation, AT SHYAMBAZAR 5 POINT CROSSING(NORTH), AT 18:16 HRS VIDE CASE NO- crPC019286/16 DATED 06-DEC-16. FOR ONLINE PAYMENT PLEASE VISIT https://kolkatatrafficpolice.net - TEAM KTP', '2016-12-06T14:16:54+0000', 'negative'),
