('129115403803409_1161141403951228', 'Sir,\nI received a message from \'kolpol\' on 22nd Oct,2016, the following message \n\"WB06C2887 HAS BEEN PROSECUTED FOR Light Signal Violation, AT PARAMA ISLAND, AT 16:04 HRS VIDE CASE NO- xxPC037991/16 DATED 20-OCT-16. FOR ONLINE PAYMENT PLEASE VISIT https://kolkatatrafficpolice.net - TEAM KTP\"\n\nThere must be some mistake from your end. I work at a PSU and that day I joined my office around 11-10 AM  and leave from office around 8.50 PM with my Motorcycle. I collect CCTV clipping And also saved google timeline movement.\n\nPlease advice.\n\nMriganga Chatterjee\nmrigangachatterjee@gmail.com', '2016-11-03T14:18:20+0000', 'positive'),
('129115403803409_1161281427224076', 'Dear Sir,\n\nI want to file complaint against Austin Distributors Pvt. Ltd. of Baishnabghata, Patuli. On 17-Dec-2014 I sold my car \"Maruti Esteem, Reg. No. WB-02N-9133\" to them (in exchange of buying a new car), however the same car violated traffic on 23-Mar-2016 for which the traffic ticket was issued to my name by Kolkata Traffic Department. All liabilities and responsibilities to that particular car stands to Austin Distributors Pvt. Ltd. as and on from 17-Dec-2014. Therefore, I\'m not liable to pay the fine as described in the traffic ticket. I have attached the original scanned copy of the traffic ticket and the delivery challan was issued by Austin Distributors Pvt. Ltd. along with this complain letter. I want to mention that this incident has caused me severe mental agony and stress since the traffic letter was brought to my notice. Therefore, I request you to take necessary action against Austin Distributors Pvt. Ltd. for this unlawful activity to sell the car to someone without transferring registration details to his/her name.\n\nThanking You,\nSoumik Dasgupta\n9749945541', '2016-04-11T03:33:38+0000', 'negative'),
