('129115403803409_1183769468352699', 'Respected Sir/,Madam , \n                      After calling several times and given written mails atlast getting no results I am writing on social media. This complaint is regarding Innumerable Parking in front of our premises and no action is been taken inspite of several complaint neither Local police or Traffic guard Police has taken any action. I  am astonished to see that even i dont get a reply back mail from others.\nI am Saikat Dey(RONNIE)son of Kali Mohan Dey resident of 15 Mansatala Lane, Kidderpore, Kolkata -700023. We are very old locals of our area Kidderpore.\nOur life has become miserable due to innumerable vehicle parking illegally in our lane and in spite of several complains there is no action taken by the local Police and other Authorities.\nThis parking is caused due to the illegal markets built up near Mansatala Lane all illegal contruction has been done I PLAZA, GREEN PLAZA 2 , M K PLAZA AND now a new contruction done upcoming market just beside my house 6.5 floors inside local lane named \"HongKong Trade Centre\" all these markets are illegal and i can guarantee kmc and other authorities has been bribed for all these illegal construction which has no parking facility and no proper construction. \nThere are \"No Parking\" Boards still  everyday there are several  vehicles kept in-front of our house,and creates a lot of Chaos not even an ambulance can pass due to the illegal parking both side of the lane. I there by bound to write a mail to you and other authorities without seeing any other way.\nWe are unsafe and therefore fear that anything can be kept in those vehicles which are kept illegally in the lanes. \nWhenever we call the Traffic Authorities they said  \"We will look in this matter\" however they fail to do so.\nIt\'s our earnest request please look into this matter seriously and take necessary action. \nRegards \nSaikat Dey', '2016-09-24T08:25:21+0000', 'negative'),
('129115403803409_1184580548325856', 'I work in Salt Lake sector 5 and my house is in Dhakuria.          Today while coming back from office in between 7.15pm to 7.30pm, near Science City Island, this car (Wb16N6851) suddenly swerved left without caring that  I was there in my motorcycle alongwith my wife and by god grace i somehow managed to save both of us. I followed the car and tried to stop it near the Trinamul head office but the driver attemted to flee once again by throwing us off balance again. Ultimately i managed to stop the car and managed to speak to the driver. To my horror I saw that there were 2 small kids in the front seat without seatbelt. The driver started arguing with me and so I thought I should click a picture of the car and post it here. Looking at the condition of the car it seemed that the driver is a regular rash driver. Please take immediate action against the driver and also the owner who allow such drivers to drive so recklessly.', '2017-01-12T14:30:58+0000', 'negative'),
