('129115403803409_1184897361561390', 'Got the sms from kolkata police this afternoon stating that some signal has been violated by my car WB02AH2961 at 16:35 hrs today. But the fact is i was in hotel hyatt since morning 9:30 till evening 7 pm attending nasscom conference and my car was parked in hotel parking. I enquired with hotel authorities at 16:45 and they confirmed me that car is in parking area and also showed me the keys. I request authorities to lookinto the matter and withdraw the charges. You can get confirmations from hyatt hotel also.', '2016-07-15T15:01:43+0000', 'neutral'),
('129115403803409_1185644084806352', 'Dear Kolkata Traffic Police,\n\nPlease Help us.\n\nThis is to draw your kind attention that at the GOLPARK Circle Signal, not enough time gap is available between Green-OFF signal facing South (for vehicles from AMRI Hosp stop) and Green-ON signal facing East (for vehicles from <U+09AE><U+09CC><U+099A><U+09BE><U+0995> sweet shop). \nImplementation of more time gap is necessary considering the long curved road aroud Golpark Circle. \n\nI am given the case below, in spite of green signal when I crossed stop line moving to North. However, I found the signal to Southern Avenue (on my left) just turning Green in front of my eyes by the few seconds when I reached closer to Golpark Circle. \n\nThere was no fault on my part, neither and never do I have any intention to jump signal or, commit stop-line violation. It was my bad luck timing coincidence. You will understand if cctv video is available at Golpark Circle.\n\n5 more seconds between these signals turning green will reduce my tension.\n\nPlease Help.\n\nBest Regards\n\n===========\n\"WB02AJ5824 HAS BEEN PROSECUTED FOR Stop Line Violation, AT GOLPARK/KAKULIA ROAD/, AT 08:49 HRS VIDE CASE NO- hhPC066046/16 DATED 02-NOV-16. FOR ONLINE PAYMENT PLEASE VISIT https://kolkatatrafficpolice.net - TEAM KTP\"', '2016-11-06T13:23:17+0000', 'neutral'),
