('129115403803409_1201399693281223', 'Few hours ago I was passing by the CESC south calcutta office (nearly Ballygunge Phari). I took a left turn when the signal turned yellow but a traffic guard caught me and asked for the papers. I showed all the papers including the license but still the traffic guard gave me a fine of Rs.400 and took my license away. I agree with this law. \nBut at that point of time a SX4 car with a number of 2203 broke the signal. She was caught (as the driver was a woman). She was coming from one way, she didn\'t have a license or a single document of the car. But the traffic guard gave he a fine of Rs.200. \nMy question is why the rule is not equal for everyone? I broke the signal and got a fine of Rs.400 having all the necessary documents but that car just got a fine of Rs 200 without all the necessary documents. The rule should be equal to everyone. And when I asked the traffic guard about this inequality he just waved his hand in a manner of nothing is wrong.\nBecause of some Kolkata traffic police like Mr. S Bagchi some people still hate our polices. \nPlease do take actions about this matter. \nThank you.\nPapai Saha.', '2016-12-14T11:24:24+0000', 'negative'),
