('129115403803409_1365486776832926', 'Today, 21st Aug, 2017, around 1230 pm, a contingent of Police force suddenly caught many cars on Girish Mukherjee Road, Bhawanipore for parking in a \"No-parking\" zone, with no sign boards saying that it has suddenly become a no parking zone and where people have been parking for years. That is strange, but fine as we were unaware, but what is even more absurd is that they forced people to pay the Fine of Rs 100/- with a Challan as per process and additionally, another amount of Rs 200/- for which they issued a receipt of \"Nahar Singh Crane Service\", though there was no question of towing as the driver was inside the car and moved away after being told to do so. This was done for all the cars ( 20-30 vehicles had been caught ). My question is why this extra Rs 200/- for crane service when there was no question of towing ?', '2017-08-21T15:30:44+0000', 'negative'),
