('129115403803409_1371345412899547', 'Hello Sir,  My name is Soumen Adhikary.  I had purchased an used four wheeler (Santro), registration no. WB02X 0894 in July 2014. I got my name transferred on 11th Aug 2014 in Barasat RTO. Now when I am trying to sell my car I am seeing there are close to 40 cases of Rs. 100 is appearing on the Kolkata traffic police website against my car.\n\n The issue is almost all of those incidents are before 2014. And there are only 2 cases during the period when I own the car.  The previous owner might have not paid those pending fees.  When I bought the car I checked but there were no cases appearing in the website. It seems that those have been updated later on. I got very much worried and paid those pending fees for which I got the payment option today.  Few cases with status \'court\'  are still pending (only two of those are during my ownership).  I tried to contact the previous owner, but unfortunately he  passed away. \n\nI have no other way but to seek your help in this situation. Would request you to kindly consider my issue and refund or waive off the pending fees for which I was not responsible if possible. I am attaching my smart card details here. Earnestly looking forward for your help in this regard. \n\nSoumen Adhikary \n9477569316', '2016-12-28T16:06:51+0000', 'positive'),
('129115403803409_1374091435982286', '#Two_Kolkata_Police_Sergeant_ROSE_15_And_ROSE_17Of_DH_ROAD_TP_GUARD_Is_Helping_A_Blind_Person...\n#Thank_You_Kolkata_Police....', '2017-04-10T14:18:29+0000', 'neutral'),
('129115403803409_1375737455819804', 'Dumbfounded to find a sms on 20.03.2017 from KTP stating that \" WB08A 1597 has 0 Police Case & 7 Court Cases as on 16.03.2017.To Pay and for details visit http://kolkatatrafficpolice.net” .This is to mention at the very outset, that I have not received any letter of communication from KTP regarding violation of traffic rules since I bought my car in Jan 15 nor I have been intercepted a single instance physically by any traffic officials on road in this tenure. So the sms from KTP is indeed a bit shocker for me.\n\nAs intimated, tried multiple times to check and pay online for the pending cases at the site mentioned, but could not do so due to a pop up - “Invalid Chassis No\". Surprisingly buying a new car from an authorized Maruti dealer in Kolkata, and getting a pop up of “Invalid Chassis No” in Kolkata Traffic Police site when all the details provided accurately, is really a second shocker for me.\n\n However being a responsible and law abiding citizen, I personally visited Beliaghata Traffic Guard located at Chingrighata on 20.03.2017 and was being informed that I have 7 court cases pending against my car since 2015 and they showed me the details of the cases in places in Kolkata where I less frequently travel with my car.\n\nWith doubts in my mind but to expedite the matter, I agreed on paying the necessary fines and releasing the cases levied upon my car. But to my utmost disbelief, I have been informed that I have to shell Rs.500.00 / case ie. Rs.3500.00 for 7 court cases including the fine and court official fees to settle the matter (Rs.300.00 / case as fine & Rs.200.00 / case as court fees).The entire amount can be deposited at the Traffic Police Guard and the settlement would be done within two days.\n \nBeing one of the earliest member of your facebook page and a lucky attendee of the first interaction with the facebook friends at Lalbazar with the senior police officials way back in June 2012, I genuinely have immense respect for all the members of Kolkata Traffic Police and the work they are doing 24*7 to keep the city safe and sound but again with this recent experience I really feel cheated. My car being a self driven one, I can assure that I have never taken my car to some places listed in the pending cases nor I was a traffic violator. And I am not alone; thousands of such penalties are being levied against vehicles for no reasons and people have to cough up the money as fines just to avoid further harassment.\n\nThrough this communication, I would at least like you to educate me and thousands of sufferers like me out there on how to overcome this unwelcome situation .Would humbly request you to intimate us about the exact amount to be paid as fees for the court citation cases against one’s vehicle (Signal Violation and cases like that) and both the online and offline procedure for paying the fines at the earliest to avoid future complications.\n\nThanks and Regards\n\nSwarup Saha\n9831569933', '2017-03-22T08:25:08+0000', 'positive'),
