('129115403803409_1425780864136850', 'I have came to know about case no. crPC408677/17 against my car no WB26S-8318 dated 9th August 2017 for Speed Violation at EM By Pass.\n\nThe attached image against the case no. clearly indicates its not my car as it is showing a White Scropio with Vehicle No. WB26S-9318, where as my car is a Green Chevrolet BEAT with vehicle No. WB26S-8318.\n\nI have written mail to , dctp@kolkatapolice.gov.in  to withdraw the case against my car No. WB26S-8318. But no response. Can you please help.', '2017-11-11T18:19:48+0000', 'negative'),
('129115403803409_1426106424104294', 'Today at around 08.35hrs, I had been asked to stop by the traffic guard near Ruby Hospital crossing coming from Garia route. The reason they asked me to stop was for violating the signal, which in actual was not the case. When I asked them to check the CCTV footage, they started arguing. The senior sergeant Mr. Harish Pradhan was asking his staff to forcibly raise a citation against my vehicle as I was asking the logic of stopping me, which they considered as arguing.\nWhen asked the senior sergeant that why and what’s the reason for stopping the car, he wanted to raise a spot fine,which I said that i won’t give at any cost as I did not break the signal. As I was approaching towards my office, and even after informing them the same, they were not allowing me to leave. But when they said that I am arguing with them, I said I need to write this to everyone as how the harassment is being done in the normal morning hours without any reason. \nDear Traffic team, we do consider/accept/support the rules made by the government for following the signals and we try and follow the same. But will request you all to please not to force the general public by harassing without any specific reason.\nHope others don’t suffer like this for wrong reason. Also not sure whether I will have to pay any fines as we all do sometime or the other without even knowing the actual mistake.', '2017-11-12T04:19:58+0000', 'positive'),
('129115403803409_1426175154097421', 'I wish to bring to the attention of traffic police the dangerous way in which cars are parked on both sides of the street in Middleton Row . Both sides parking is rampant from as early as 7pm especially on Saturday and Sunday. Also there\'s both side parking on the narrow kerb where the road bends to the left near Loreto house while going towards camac st. There\'s no space for two cars to pass especially after 10pm\nWe the residents have to always take the risk of accidents while returning home\nKP just turns a blind eye to this issue. I am sure it can only happen in collusion with the local PS', '2017-11-12T06:39:16+0000', 'negative'),
('129115403803409_1426193330762270', 'I need to cross Singhabari crossing(Near Metro Cash & Carry) on weekdays to drop my child at bus stand at around 7:45am. Pedestrian crossing & vehicle movement from non-bypass roads signal opens for only 5secs. Its really very hard to cross road with in 5secs. Some accident might happen due to this as several children cross road to catch school bus. I have intimated on duty offer also but as per him its centrally controlled. It cant be changed. This crossing interval increases after 8am. Can you please increase this interval to at least 15 secs between 7am and 8am.', '2017-11-12T07:13:07+0000', 'negative'),
('129115403803409_1426264030755200', 'I got an sms that my motorcycle has been prosecuted for riding without helmet at cit road/ ananda palit crossing on 5.11.2017 sunday at 8.30 am . At that time I was sleeping and my motor cycle was under garage condition form 3.11.2017 ie friday night. \nUnder this circumstance how could my vehicle be prosecuted for riding without helmet??\nIt is my kind request to verify this type of false cases.\nAttatchment of the sms I got\n\"WB01AJ2981 has been prosecuted for Without Helmet, at CIT ROAD/ANANDA PALIT ROAD/, at 08:31 hrs vide case no- ooTW234661/17 dated 05-NOV-17. For online payment please visit https://kolkatatrafficpolice.net - TEAM KTP\"', '2017-11-12T09:09:02+0000', 'positive'),
