('129115403803409_1427543210627282', 'Dear sir,\nThis is to bring your notice that, i got two sms, as details are given below\n\nWB02AG5373 has been prosecuted for Light Signal Violation, at E M BYPASS/CANAL SOUTH ROAD/SALTLAKE BYPASS, at 07:16 hrs vide case no- mmPC119205/17 dated 13-NOV-17. For online payment please visit https://kolkatatrafficpolice.net - TEAM KTP\n\nWB02AG5373 HAS BEEN PROSECUTED FOR Light Signal Violation, AT S P SARANI/RAWDON STREET/, AT 17:16 HRS VIDE CASE NO- ggPC127519/17 DATED 03-SEP-17. FOR ONLINE PAYMENT PLEASE VISIT https://kolkatatrafficpolice.net - TEAM KTP\n\nBut my car has been parked in the garage on both days and even i never went at SP SARANI/ ROWDON STREET with this car.\n\nPlease look into this matter\n\nThanks\nPrasun Chakraborty\n9874059809', '2017-11-13T20:49:00+0000', 'neutral'),
('129115403803409_1427642110629558', 'The Dy. Commissioner of Police\nTraffic Department.\n\nDear Sir(s),\nI am Gautam Bhattacharjee working with CESC and residing at 21/1D Fern Road, Kolkata 700019. Car no. WB02AJ0265.\n\nI am in receipt of a traffic violation case, the snap shot of which has been attached to this post.\n\nMy humble submission is that on 19 April\'17 my car did not go out of my garage and the location that has been mentioned, has not been visited by me (CGR Rd etc) ever since I came out of the emergency / operational job in CESC, way back in 1996 !\n\nOn a previous occasion, the same location was given, however I did not protest and paid Rs. 100/- on line. But this time i thought it to be prudent to raise the issue.\n\nWould request a kind attention please.\n\nThanks & regards,\nGautam Bhattacharjee', '2017-05-20T08:17:47+0000', 'positive'),
('129115403803409_1427721207276149', 'Yesterday morning I was riding down the VIP road at around 6:10 am, heading towards ultadanga. Near the Laketown crossing where a U turn has been created to take a turn towards laketown, a bus plying on the route 215A took a U turn from the extreme left flank of the road to extreme right(have attached a picture  for reference). I was on the middle lane on my scooty near the rear wheels of the bus, the bus rammed my scooty, my scooty crashed down near the right  rear tyre of the bus & I suffered injuries. I would like to mention that the bus didn’t give any indication that it would take a right turn, no side indicator was put on neither he made a manual indication by waving his hand & all this time I kept on honking to make the bus driver realise that I was on the right of the bus & the bus turn would result in ramming into my scooty. I approached the traffic guard at the crossing who although witnessed the accident denied to lodge a complaint on the pretext that the vehicle has not sustained any damage . To quote him he said “vehicle has not been damaged so case can’t be lodged” although I have suffered injuries & I may have even lost my life because of this errant driver. The traffic guard was infact helping out the errant driver to flee away with the bus, he neither took a complaint , he even didn’t  take down the number of the bus, rather he kept on fighting with me that I need to move out my vehicle so that the bus is not held up . I was forced to dial 100 on which police sergeants from Bidhannagar police station came down & helped me to lodge a complaint at the Laketown police station. I am herein attaching the video footage of the traffic guard & also the bus details which rammed against my scooty. My question is “Is human life so inexpensive that an errant driver can’t be booked because the vehicle in question is not damaged although the rider has been injured or could have died?” How long will the common people suffer because of such unruly drivers who are menacing down the city roads flouting every possible norm\'s?\nWill police only take action only after someone is dead?', '2017-11-14T02:38:15+0000', 'negative'),
('129115403803409_1427775093937427', 'This truck has been lying for more than one week at the entry of the Ekbalpore lane under Ekbalpore P.S as the lane is 2way with this truck there is not enough space for both side vehicle to move easily and creating a jam please sir requesting you to remove the vehicle from this space for convenience of the resident.', '2017-11-14T04:15:07+0000', 'neutral'),
