('129115403803409_1427815610600042', '#KolkataTrafficPolice ....appreciate the way you guys handle the traffic at VIP Kaikhali more...wis this happens every day to keep traffic smooth', '2017-11-14T05:30:54+0000', 'positive'),
('129115403803409_1427820943932842', 'Among your awareness program regarding unnecessary honking I\'m sharing today\'s experience.\n\nA Tata sumo with no. WB26S3531 with POLICE sticker all around and a blinker in front was behind me and was honking unnecessarily. The stretch was full with traffic and there was no way for anybody to give  way even if they desire. \nDate 14.11.17, time 9:35am, location between tollygunge metro to tollygunge phari.\n\nI think you should lead by example.\n\nAlso I\'ve not heard anything regarding another of my complaint regarding overspeeding of a car WB02AF9115 with police sticker  opposite salt lake stadium which was posted more than a month ago. \n\nBoth the cars are obviously private vehicle.\n\nSo if I get a police sticker on my car will I be  exempt from all traffic rules?\n\nPlease enlighten me.', '2017-11-14T05:40:35+0000', 'positive'),
('129115403803409_1427833547264915', 'Private cars are being parked on the sidewalk every day under Lifeline Nursing Home on Wood Street and Short Street Crossing. \n\nThis photograph was taken at 1110 AM today. Car No: WB02 AF 1445 is a habitual offender. \n\nThis forces people to walk on the road and causes unnecessary traffic slowdown and honking. This is my 4th complaint about cars being parked on the sidewalk. Requesting your able team to look into this matter.', '2017-11-14T06:08:48+0000', 'negative'),
('129115403803409_1427847963930140', 'Today I got below SMS from Kolkata traffic police :\n\"WB24Y5711 has been prosecuted for No Parking, at AJC BOSE ROAD/RAWDON STREET/, at 12:50 hrs vide case no- ggPC139250/17 dated 06-NOV-17. For online payment please visit https://kolkatatrafficpolice.net - TEAM KTP\". \nBut the main thing is my home is almost 40 km away from Kolkata. I stay in Bangalore. My family is in West Bengal and my elder brother is suffering from malaria from last Saturday. None else can drive car in my house and none took out my car from my home as well. We last used our car on the day of Kalipujo and that too in very near by location. I don\'t know how kolkata traffic police caught my car in a no parking zone which is very away from my home. Is it kind of mistake ? Is there any CCTV footage to recheck the number of the car? Shall I have to pay the fine without committing any mistake? Can you help me in this regard, #kolkatatrafficpolice ? \n\nHoping to get justice.\n\nThanks and regards.\nSoumya Biswas', '2017-11-14T06:38:07+0000', 'positive'),
('129115403803409_1427890850592518', 'It\'s good to see Kolkata police and citizens are spreading awareness for no horn.. I would like to ask what other options vehicle have if they don\'t horn? Pedestrian walk on roads, shops are there in footpath both things don\'t match. Pedestrian should get proper space to walk on footpath then honking will automatically decrease. Not only hawkers are an issue roadside parking too..', '2017-11-14T08:07:46+0000', 'positive'),
('129115403803409_1427919200589683', 'Today At about 1:45 PM I met a lady named Akhtari Begum at the road just outside of the PG Hospital, Kolkata who has lost her 16 years old girl Anjuma Khatun (who is under treatment of mental deptt of P G hospital according to Akhtati and wearing a red garment at about 1:15PM) .She resides at Beltala,, Ranihati. \n\nShe was crying with fear.She approached me for help. I informed the matter to the helpline number 100. And took her to the police outpost at PG hospital.The officials directed her to report the matter to Bhawanipore PS.She contacted some of her relative may be, with my mobile who\'s number  is 9734919702.\nAll I just could do,boarded her into a bus for Bhawanipore PS as I had go for my duty.\n \nPLEASE HELP HER.', '2017-11-14T09:05:21+0000', 'negative'),
('129115403803409_1427938260587777', 'Today at about 1:40PM I met a lady named Akhtari Begum just at the road outside of PG Hospital, Kolkata who has lost her 16 years old girl Anjuma Khatun at about 1:15PM(who is a mental patient of PG hospital wearing a red dress according to Akhtari)  inside of the hospital while in queue for medicine etc.She reside at Beltala, Ranihati. Akhtari was crying in fear and approached for help. \nI informed the matter to the helpline number 100 and took her to the police outpost at PG Hospital. The officials directed her to report the matter to the Bhowanipir PS.\nAll I could do that,boarded her into the bus for Bhowanipor PS as I had to go for my duty. \n\nShe contacted with some of her relative may be, with my mobile who\'s number is 9734919702.\nAgain I repeated the whole matter to the helpline number 100.\nI hope Kolkata police will response in this case as before all of my personal experiences.. \n\nToday is Children\'s day.. Please help a lost child to reach her parents.', '2017-11-14T09:43:05+0000', 'negative'),
('129115403803409_1427958333919103', 'Online Payment Link not working on the http://kolkatatrafficpolice.gov.in website for many days now. Is there an alternative to check and pay traffic violation fines?', '2017-11-14T10:22:01+0000', 'neutral'),
('129115403803409_1427959680585635', 'Today 14/11/2017 i was driving my car from majerhat bridge towards mominpur. My car speed was around 45 kmph. As soon I got down from majerhat a little further sergeant stopped me and said my speed was 50 in the manual machine which other person was handling. Now there are no proper signage over there and on a vacant road what do you expect to drive at 40 kmph. Which he told was the max speed allowed. He took 300 Rs spot fine and gave me the reciept. \n\nWhat do you expect from us to remember different speed limits at different roads. Somewhere it’s 40 somewhere it’s 50 and somewhere it’s 60. Is it possible to remember the speed limits everywhere. And by driving at 40 on vacant roads the roads will become more jam. It’s not the solution. \n\nWhy don’t you all issue a uniform speed limit for entire kolkata. That will be easy for everybody to remember. \n\nFrom my side what I paid today was wrong. I should not have been charged for this.', '2017-11-14T10:24:31+0000', 'negative'),
('129115403803409_1427983487249921', 'Sir,\nPrivate cars are being parked on the sidewalk every day under Lifeline Nursing Home on Wood Street and Short Street Crossing. \n\nThis photograph was taken just a couple of minutes before making this post.\n\nCar No: WB06 D 0941 flaunting a police sign on the dashboard inside the care can be seen parked on the sidewalk.\n\nI made a similar post this morning where a different car was parked in the same spot. Seems to me that your local beat is up to making some little money on the side?\n\nWhat action is going to be taken on this Police Car?', '2017-11-14T11:07:40+0000', 'negative'),
('129115403803409_1428002940581309', 'I had asked this question on 11th November, 2017. I have not received any response yet. I am once again asking the same question with a request to kindly answer the same.....\n\nIs Free Left Turn allowed when the Traffic Signal is Red and there are no signage of NO FREE LEFT / NO INFILTRATION LEFT ?', '2017-11-14T11:37:45+0000', 'negative'),
('129115403803409_1428037693911167', 'My Name is Dr-Asad Jamal Khan I think by mistake you have  provided me this message.As the day was a Sunday my two wheeler was in the garage.And I was present somewhere else...I have got the attendance report of that....So one person can\'t be at two places at the same time.I think there is some mis understanding from your end....If not then plz provide me Video evidence.', '2017-11-14T12:27:13+0000', 'neutral'),
('129115403803409_1428044640577139', 'Again !! No proof against this case !! Withdraw this case immediately .....', '2017-11-14T12:38:25+0000', 'neutral'),
('129115403803409_1428230820558521', 'WB01AB4030 has been prosecuted for without helmet, at CGR Road/Sick Line Xing/, at 12.33 hrs vide case no-jjTW055435/17 dated 07-NOV-17\n\nSir can you please share the images as the image is not available on the http://kolkatatrafficpolice.net as the vehicle was in Garage on that date.', '2017-11-14T16:58:24+0000', 'neutral'),
('129115403803409_1428249433889993', 'Dear Sir,\n\nToday while coming from Rash behari Avenue toward Jadu Babu\'s Bazar. A route bus had crashed into my vehicle. The apparent body damage though minimal, however the damage to my left front tyre is maximum. I request you to kindly go through the CCTV footage and take necessary action against the vehicle. The time of impact is 9:55 PM ~ 10:00 PM. The police at Bhowanipur PS had already noted the number. I humbly request you to check the CCTV footage and take necessary action.', '2017-11-14T17:26:31+0000', 'neutral'),
('129115403803409_1428270310554572', 'Got the following sms: ”WB06H3346 has been prosecuted for Stop Line Violation, at PRINCE ANWAR SHAH ROAD/RAJA SUBODH CHANDRA MALLICK ROAD/, at 09:06 hrs vide case no- ttPC095826/17 dated 13-NOV-17. For online payment please visit https://kolkatatrafficpolice.net - TEAM KTP\"\n\nNow my point of objection is tomorrow the whole day my car was in the workshop for repair in Oxytown, Behala .... It has been taken from our residence in Sarsuna Satellite Township around 9 am to the Oxytown workshop which is merely 3 kms from our home and the whole day servicing has been done on the car. So, how it is possible for my car to be present at Prince Anwar Shah Road around 9 am on 13th Nov ? In some of earlier cases I was given a  photographic proof taken by on road cctv .... Can I get a copy of such traffic rule violation photograph for this incidents also so that KP can prove the claim of this case ??', '2017-11-14T17:54:35+0000', 'neutral'),
('129115403803409_1428494500532153', 'On way to airport. Entire Majher Hat bridge jam bcuz of 2 trucks broken down on the bridge. Please do something immediately. \n\nJam has started from Ajanta cinema hall. Everything is standstill. Most people will miss their flights or trains.', '2017-11-15T00:20:22+0000', 'negative'),
('129115403803409_1428592390522364', 'Hi, I don\'t understand the logic behind 1PM one way change in Central Business District (mostly park Street , theater road area) it creates chaos in the entire city during that time. We face a lot of problems everyday while commuting.', '2017-11-15T03:16:22+0000', 'positive'),
('129115403803409_1428621670519436', 'Thanks Kolkata police for fining me 100rs, for riding bike without rear view mirrors.\n\nI appreciate your efforts to make roads safer in sun and dust, even when we risk our own life due to our own lethargy and negligence.\n\nWell done! <ed><U+00A0><U+00BD><ed><U+00B1><U+008F><ed><U+00A0><U+00BC><ed><U+00BF><U+00BB><ed><U+00A0><U+00BD><ed><U+00B1><U+008F><ed><U+00A0><U+00BC><ed><U+00BF><U+00BB>', '2017-11-14T13:13:39+0000', 'negative'),
