('129115403803409_1428806103834326', 'Dear Kolkata Traffic Police, I request you to update your mobile app Bondhu for Android. Once I open \"Know Your Pending Traffic Cases\" the app directs to my browser : Google Chrome. As soon as I fill all the details & click on \"Get OTP\" a disclaimer type notification comes saying \"Invalid chassis no.\" \n\nThis is my 2nd complain for the same. first was on Twitter to which I\'m still waiting for a response.\n\nHope this time it\'s taken into consideration with immediate effect.', '2017-11-15T10:06:01+0000', 'positive'),
('129115403803409_1428819760499627', 'This is with utmost & deep regret that I wish to bring to your kind notice, a very unfortunate incident, which I, Somdev Duttagupta, my wife & my 17 month old son had to face at Mandeville Gardens-Ekdalia Crossing (near South Point Junior School Exit) today morning dated 15th Nov, 2017 at around 11:40 A.M.\n\nWe had gone to pick up our toddler from his Montessori school in the same stretch of Road, like all other days, in our Car, and were returning home taking our usual route via Mandeville-Ekdalia Crossing. Since we are very well aware that the entire stretch of road remains busy with school leaving children of various ages, our car speed limit always remained within 20 Kms / hour. \n\nHowever, we do apologize, while mentioning the fact that our car may have just nicked unintentionally at one of the mini-conical Blue-White Standees at the road which was placed in the middle of the road and was almost invisible, since it was raining and the road, as understandably, was crowded by parents & their home bound children.\n\nThe Officer on Duty along with his colleague immediately beckoned us to stop the car by the road side which, I did without any hesitation. \n\nTo our utter dismay the officer in question very rudely asked me to come out of the car & literally ordered me in a very harsh and threatening tone to put the conical standee back in place while constantly accusing me of a possibility of destroying a govt property.\n\nFirstly, we wish to bring to your kind notice that we did not, under any circumstance, destroy any govt property as alleged by the officer on duty. However, what we found very objectionable and demeaning was the tone and the way in which the officer was treating me & my wife.\n\nAny self-respecting citizen would have found the behaviour very rowdy & unworthy of a person wearing a Uniform that epitomize public safety. Hence, I refused to place back the standee while pleading him time & again that he could note down my car number and register a case if at all applicable. We being knowledgeable, educated & respectful citizens, found your officer treating us literally in a very servile manner and all the while threatening to lodge a case against us using the phrase like “EMON CASE DEBO, DEKHBEN !”.\n\nI find this attitude of your officer very vindictive and absolutely unworthy of his uniform. I have even made him aware during the conversation that all of these are getting recorded in his camcorder but he was quite dismissive about it. The worst part was that, he was treating my wife in an absolutely disrespectful manner. When I had demanded to know his name & speak to his senior, he refused to co-operate, turning a deaf ear to us. His Name-tag was not visible on his uniform, however we could catch a glimpse of his colleague’s name tag ending with “Mishra”. \n\nWe had also told him that our toddler son was waiting in the car, but he showed no humanity to our plight. We have very high opinion & respect regarding the functioning of Kolkata Traffic Police Department all along which we even told your officer unequivocally. \n\nHowever, today’s incident has lead us to raise few questions against the functioning of few officers like him of your department who are actually tarnishing the department’s image.\n\nWe, ourselves, could have easily recorded today’s incident. However, as responsible citizens, we refrained from doing so. We know that Kolkata Traffic Police has always extended their arms to help out the citizens, however the attitude of this particular officer was not of assistance, co-operation or understanding. Rather it was Harassing, Vindictive and severely insulting to a family who happen to be socially responsible.      \n\nWe would like to request your team to make an immediate inquiry into the matter so that such incidents do not make a recurrence & school returning parents are not unnecessarily harassed by Officers on Duty of the area. \n\nThank you. \nYours respectfully.', '2017-11-15T10:32:20+0000', 'negative'),
