('129115403803409_1429033917144878', 'Hello... Greetings for the day... We have been facing a serious problem for the last few days. The stretch in question is Metropolitan Co-Operative Housing Bus Stop, between Chingrighata and Mathpukur. A Service road has been constructed shunting from E M Byepass just after Captain Bhery and joining back to the Byepass AFTER crossing the RED SIGNAL at Metropolitan. Recently a portion of the road has been cordoned off for metro construction. While we do understand that \"Today\'s Pain is Tomorrow\'s Gain\", passengers getting down from Science City bound traffic are having to cross the road precariously, without a STOP Signal to control traffic. Busses are dropping Passengers beyond the service road, and the commuters are having to cross the service road, as well as the bypass. Traffic in Byepass stops for a red light, but since there is no traffic control on the service road, elders and youngsters alike are having to run and jump between heavy traffic to cross. You know better than anyone else how beautifully respectful our drivers are towards pedestrians. It can easily lead to a major accident involving loss of lives... ANYTIME NOW! I would, therefore, urge you to consider placing a traffic signal on the service road, or man the area to control traffic till an overpass/underpass can be constructed. Please refer to the attached map for details on the location.', '2017-11-15T15:42:22+0000', 'negative'),
