('129115403803409_1429516930429910', 'Ref: crPC604659/17\nThis might be the second or third time that I have been prosecuted for stop line violation at Hazra Crossing(South) while heading towards my office near High Court. Kindly don\'t get me wrong. I am not saying that I didn\'t do it or entering into any contradiction thereto. I am fine with your fines, really. In fact I have already paid it. Its just that we do not possess superhuman powers to stop a momentum of a 800-1500 kgs vehicle at the very change of traffic light when there is no timer for the active green light. I wish we could because that would be amazing! The yellow light exists for a fraction of second and when the light turns red I find myself in the middle of the crossing. Please add a timer to the green light just like that of the red or atleast expand the time for the yellow light. I appreciate all the efforts of the traffic police and while managing traffic during festivities or otherwise. Its really commendable.', '2017-11-16T05:33:54+0000', 'positive'),
