('129115403803409_1429897037058566', 'I\'ve asked a simple question innumerable.times but to no avail. Why so many illegal parkings like from Posta to Girish Park are allowed in the city? These choke the traffic. Now we can see parking on MG Road too. Wherever you go, you find vehicles, both personal and commercial parked on the road. Earlier this was restricted to lanes but day by day it is becoming a menace.', '2017-11-16T16:31:24+0000', 'negative'),
('129115403803409_1429975117050758', 'This is regarding a very important topic which I would like to speak out on this page. I am one of those people who are very much concerned about their safety while driving or riding on the streets . According to The Motor Vehicles Act 1988 it has been made mandatory to use an ISI Certified helmet while riding a two wheelers on Indian roads and it is illegal to use a headgear without having an ISI Certification. However some of us are there who prefers to wear a much more safer and costlier helmet bearing atleast a DOT or ECE Cerfitication. As because these helmets are imported from foreign countries, these do not come with an ISI mark . \n Now the problem which we face sometimes on the roads are harassment and penalties by the cops . We appreciate your initiative of forcing people to wear an ISI Certified helmet . But due to lack of knowledge few cops dont understand the DOT or the ECE mark on our helmets .\n      I would like to request you to have a look on this matter and let us use these high safety helmets on the roads.\nThank you.', '2017-11-16T18:22:10+0000', 'negative'),
('129115403803409_1430058930375710', 'Thank you Kolkata Police for understanding a major problem of mine.I would like to inform you that i was on my two wheeler and was little confused whether a left turn was allowed or not.It was little guarded on that for construction works,No signal were given there and neither any sign boards .I stopped for a second and asked an on duty officer that i can take a turn or not .That particular officer and chased me out from there with an abusive language.This incident happened in Behala Chowrastha between 8 to 9pm.What i did was i went straight just after two signals i saw two sergeant officer on duty.I parked my scooter at a corner and complained to the Sergeant about the entire and that i was abused by an officer for asking whether im allowed to left turn or not...I told them about the behavior of that particular officer.Both the sergeant  did apologised to me from his side.I respect KP alot .I got helped from them whenever i required and I am very much happy of the present situation.But one thing,We are the citizens of the India.We expect a certain kind of decency from the gems who serves India..I love my Nation,and equality should be maintained by all. Thank you so much KP for taking quite action of the incident which happened. RESPECT TO THOSE SERGEANTS WHO TOOK MY ISSUE AS A SERIOUS NOTE.\nTHANK U SIR.', '2017-11-16T20:34:47+0000', 'positive'),
