('129115403803409_1432267540154849', 'I am sad to write that Kolkata Traffic Police facebook page, Kolkata Traffic police DC (south) and DC traffic Mr S Nesakumar all were informed about a wrong citation against my car no WB 02 M 9241 . This Facebook page told me DC traffic had waived off the case but the case is still showing pending. \nI wrote to DC Traffic and DC South (Traffic) informing about the case but no answer came. Not even a reply.\nMr Tapas Manna OC Purba Jadavpur Traffic Guard assured me that he had sent a request to the concerned authority to remove the citation from the internet but nothing happened. Requesting all again to do justice. Here is the copy of the communication which is very old.\n\"Kolkata Traffic Police\nJuly 26 · \nSmarajit Mukhopadhyay .. .In ref. to Memo No. FB592 dated 17.07.17, we have received your Facebook complaint and have examined it. After enquiry, DC Traffic, Kolkata has considered the instant case against the vehicle and you need not pay the fine. You are requested to verify the same by visiting the website of Kolkata Traffic Police. Inconvenience, if any is regretted.\n\nSmarajit Mukhopadhyay\nLike\nShow more reactions\nComment\nShare\nTop Comments\n4 You and 3 others\nComments\nSmarajit Mukhopadhyay\n\nWrite a comment...\nChoose File\nSmarajit Mukhopadhyay\nSmarajit Mukhopadhyay Please respond at the earliest. The citation will go to the court.\nLikeShow more reactions · Reply · September 4 at 1:48pm\nManage\nSmarajit Mukhopadhyay\nSmarajit Mukhopadhyay Thank you Sir for this prompt action to deliver justice. I have checked the website where the same case is still showing as UNPAID CITATION CASES .\nLikeShow more reactions · Reply · July 27 at 8:10am\nManage\nSmarajit Mukhopadhyay\nSmarajit Mukhopadhyay Hello Kolkata Traffic Police. Please confirm that as the case is still showing what i should do? If it remains unpaid it will go to the court and add to my trouble. Please respond.\nLikeShow more reactions · Reply · August