('129115403803409_1433879579993645', 'This is front of Beleghata Police Station in CIT more where I stay. The police station has turned the main road into a vehicle impound junkyard. Narrowing the lanes and this poses an extreme risk to us locals driving here regularly. Requesting you to please see into this with urgency and get the vehicles removed from the road. Have complained earlier as well but no action taken. Have tagged others in the locality as well.', '2017-11-21T05:59:22+0000', 'negative'),
('129115403803409_1433898829991720', 'Please find below the pictures of two traffic constables who are doing their so called duty infront of China Mandir. They catches targeted bikes and cars and ask for money and in case people deny money they will give different varities of cases to the drivers. They dont recognise car papers as well properly and if you protest They even threat people that they are quite close to the local MLA or Bidhayak or whatever he is. Would suggest to take action immediately . Shame !!', '2017-11-21T06:37:59+0000', 'negative'),
('129115403803409_1433959999985603', 'Please note that my Car No. WB02AH6051 has been prosecuted for \"HAND SIGNAL VIOLATION\" vide case No. ggPC141867/17 on 10.11.17 and for \"NO Parking\" vide case No.  ggPC140775/17 on 13.11.17. Both cases at Rawdon Street/La Martina School. This is nothing but harassment to the parents. In the maddening traffic around the school with cars coming from 2 directions, how practical is it for the Police to issue case for a Hand Signal Violation ? Who will prove the same ? And please tell me where my driver is parking the Car and getting so many \"No Parking\" Cases slapped as I never ever have found a place to park before the Police come running to me shouting to remove the car. Also, i have not received any response to the earlier complains on similar cases sent over email to \'dctp@kolkatatrafficpolice.gov.in\'', '2017-11-21T08:53:57+0000', 'neutral'),
('129115403803409_1433973873317549', 'At present I am sitting in my office at Salt Lake Sector-V. I entered office at about 9:00 AM driving my car WB-06-J-4604.\nHowever, I received a SMS (see image) a few minutes back about a \"No Parking\" violation at \"Park Street/Middleton Row/F.S.Street\" when I have not been in the area at all.\nCan the Kolkata Traffic Police clarify how this is possible?\nThis is a gross mistake and would request KTP to either close or delete this case from the system.\n\nOr is this a scam to generate funds for the Kolkata Traffic Police?\n\nIf such mistakes are common then what recourse do the common man have?', '2017-11-21T09:21:27+0000', 'negative'),
