('129115403803409_1434237063291230', 'Why don’t you regulate the govt vehicles which does not go through designated lanes and even do not stop at proper bus stops.I see people running to catch them .You are the reason why accidents have not reduced.Traffic fines have become revenue model for the state whereas its main purpose is different. State bus drivers are never fined for not obeying the traffic laws.', '2017-11-21T16:01:17+0000', 'positive'),
('129115403803409_1434254956622774', 'An excellent experience received from Kolkata Traffic Police.  At around 8 in the evening today, my Car was stuck in peak traffic at the middle of road at Beliaghata Eastern bypass traffic signal. I was alone with no idea of car mechanism.  Car steering was locked and break jammed.  Car not moving at all. About 500 cars were stuck resulting in a traffic chaos . I was puzzled.  But within few minutes from somewhere a traffic surgeant and a constable  came. They were so cooperative and helpful. They kept on telling me not to worry and was always very polite in spite of excessive traffic pressure on them. They alerted me about possible theft of my articles from the car. They remained beside me for about 45 min as I was waiting for Maruti on road personnel to come. They helped me to start the vehicle and also bade good night to me. I convey my sincere gratitude to those officials through this media.', '2017-11-21T16:27:08+0000', 'negative'),
('129115403803409_1434280389953564', 'Today again I experienced a Gr8 tragedy/audacity because of our Administrative inefficiencies, I believe!\nAutos in Kolkata choosing their passengers as per their wish & will! Passengers are being badly compromising helplessly!\nOn Complaint Traffic Surgeons found advising passengers to lodge Complaint in local PS? \nWhether that act of Traffic Surgeons are Constitutional?\nCan the Administrator\'s have the answers on their act?\nTraffic police are always being found bussy with collection. Is that traffic police being made for the same?\nIs that the act is primary requirement on road safety?\nCan a healthy civilization be expected from the Traffic policing?', '2017-11-21T17:06:21+0000', 'negative'),
('129115403803409_1434287043286232', 'THERE IS A PROBLEM IN SIGNALLING ON THE ROAD IN FRONT OF R G KAR HOSPITAL.\n\nTHE NORTH BOUND VEHICLES COMING FROM EAST THROUGH THE CANAL SIDE HAVE TO CROSS THAT ROAD WITHOUT ANY SORTS OF SIGNALLING MOST OF THE TIME. CHANCE OF ACCIDENT IS MORE\n\nPL LOOK INTO THIS.', '2017-11-21T17:17:59+0000', 'negative'),
('129115403803409_1434289963285940', 'THERE IS A SIGNALLING ISSUE AT THE CROSSING OF ARABINDA SARANI AND RAJA DINENDRA STREET.\n\nTHE NORTH BOUND VEHICLES COMING FROM EAST VIA ARABINDA SARANI HAVE TO TURN RIGHT TO RAJA DINENDRA STREET TOGETHER WITH THOSE WHICH ARE GOING FROM WEST TO EAST ON THE ARABINDA SARANI.\n\nPL LOOK INTO THIS.\n\nBTW, SIMILAR SITUATION IS THERE AT THE CROSSING OF BIBEKANANDA ROAD AND RAJA DINENDRA STREET. BUT THERE THE SIGNALLING IS ABSOLUTELY FINE.', '2017-11-21T17:23:07+0000', 'negative'),
('129115403803409_1434294483285488', 'THE CARS COMING TOWARDS NORTH THROUGH THE SERVICE ROAD BETWEEN MANI SQUARE MALL AND BENGAL CHEMUCAL CROSSING, ARE NOT ALLOWED TO TURN RIGHT TO AVAIL EM BYPASS.\n\nTHEY ARE FORCED TO TAKE THE SERVICE ROAD FURTHER CROSSING THE MANICKTALA MAIN ROAD.\n\nPL CHECK THE CONDITION OF THAT SERVICE ROAD. IT IS ABSOLUTELY HORRIBLE.\n\nREQUEST YOU TO ALLOW THE VEHICLES TO TURN RIGHT TILL THAT SERVICE ROAD IS GETTING READY.', '2017-11-21T17:28:34+0000', 'neutral'),
('129115403803409_1434297343285202', 'THE NORTH BOUND VEHICLES COMING FROM SOUTH HAVE TO FACE 3 CONSECUTIVE TRAFFIC SIGNALS NEAR RUBY HOSPITAL CROSSING.\n\nTHE CONSTABLE POSTED AT THE FIRST TRAFFIC SIGNAL, ALLOWS THE VEHICLE TO GO STRAIGHT WHEN THE SIGNAL IS RED AND STOPS IT WHEN THE SIGNAL IS GREEN. \n\nREALLY CANT UNDERSTAND THE LOGIC BEHIND IT.', '2017-11-21T17:32:31+0000', 'positive');
