('129115403803409_1437330462981890', 'Kolkata Traffic Police - Dear KTP,\nThis is further to my phone call to 1073 on 22nd Nov 08.41 AM.\nKindly refer the location (22.541363, 88.333520) AJC Bose Road towards Rabindra Sadan near Zeerut Bridge xing opposite to Army Quarters.\nIt is extremely dangerous / difficult for drivers coming down from Vidyasagar Setu to recognise sudden vehicles coming out of Army Qtrs and taking the AJC Bose Road towards R. Sadan. Mainly because trees/bush on the divider blocks our vision (particularly for small cars at lower eye level) \nMorning time, Army Constables (M.P.) are there BUT they make a tactical mistake as they stand right at their gate (i.e. opposite side of the AJC Bose road 22.541300,88.333475).\nResult is - Neither men on duty can see small cars coming down from Setu near that Xing not the car drivers can see whether any  vehicle is coming out of army gate.\nI somehow averted an accident on 22nd and immediately called 1073.\nRequest - please ask your person or Army Persons on duty to stand at the divider point 22.541363, 88.333520; (where from they can see both side of AJC Bose road) for a safer traffic control.  \n(incidentally, in the evening, I find KTP persons always stand at the divider only - rightly).', '2017-11-25T04:45:34+0000', 'negative'),
