('129115403803409_1439100676138202', 'Hello! team KTP, \n\nThis post is to make you aware of the traffic situation( and to take remedial steps) at/around Rajabazar Tram depot on the sealdah/moulali bound lane, every morning. \n\nYou force pvt. buses to go through the bus lane till Sealdah flyover(Bidyapati Setu), at their own sweet pace.... But you allow all WBTC buses on the outside lane. \nThis creates the long Que till rajabazar tram depot and beyond affecting movement of all vehicles including cabs, pvt. cars.  The traffic personnel posted there, do not allow buses to take the outside lane, even if he sees there is a huge chaos...\nThe footpaths(where exists) beside this bus lane are occupied and restricts movement of pedestrians to get on the buses.. Its risky too to walk on the road beside moving buses, with cycle, bike, vans parked there. \nI have personally approached many of the on-duty traffic Sargent posted there..unfortunately without any result. I sincerely request you to look into your CCTV footage...should help you. \nEven in October it used to be a 10-12 min bus ride till moulali from rajabazar x-ing....now its approx. 20 mins. \n\nHope to see better days ahead. Thanks & best regards.', '2017-11-27T07:55:23+0000', 'neutral'),
