('129115403803409_1439564732758463', 'Today I was returning from office, Wipro Kolkata to my home at Madurdaha, Kolkata 107. A white Scorpio variant(WB38AA0501) had hit my car (WB22U 3875) at around 9 pm by taking a sharp left turn 100 meters before the Ruby General hospital. I tried to stop the driver/car in several ways but the driver deliberately ran away. I have no concrete proof that I could have used to report this incident to police immediately, but I am frustrated that such drivers are driving on the roads and making the roads unsafe for others. Thought of sharing this with you.', '2017-11-27T20:20:15+0000', 'neutral'),
('129115403803409_1439742576074012', 'Dear Kolkata Police : when i was reading today\'s news paper in the morning I was just shocked ... i was was thinking I could have been in that accident, my photo could have  been published as a victim ! We ,the general people travelling through public vehicles always see rush driving/dangerous overtaking when we are just inside that vehicle and driver/conducter just don\'t listen to us ! \nI travel in shuttle (traveller) everyday from Patuli to sector-v and found 2/3 such drivers who runs always with heavy high speed plush rush driving. One day I told I am am going to complain and the answer I got \"no police can do any thing to me ..go and tell my name\" . I got down at college more and told about the incident  to the traffic inspector standing there..and the answer I got from traffic inspector was \"you can go to police station and lodge your complaint\"  ! So why they can do anything ..they are just there to maintain traffic, making challans only ! \nIf we take necessary action prior to the incident this thing won\'t happen sir . I am pretty sure one day we will see those car also in this news paper like today !\nSenior police officer should do something for us ! And traffic inspector alos can do so manything (not just telling us to go to.police station to file a complaint)\nWe general prople don\'t have body guard/red-blue light car ..so we are in high risk Sir!\nI am not worried for me ... I am worried for my kid (I feel all police officers think like that way ), \nWHAT WOULD HAPPEN TO MY KID IF I  NOT ALIVE TOMORROW  !!! <ed><U+00A0><U+00BD><ed><U+00B9><U+008F>', '2017-11-28T01:44:53+0000', 'neutral'),
('129115403803409_1439830202731916', 'One particular stretch of EM Bypass- from Fortis to Tagore Park, is facing huge traffic congestion every day during rush hours due to not building a culvert which could have solved the bottleneck problem here. \nThe authorities for some unknown reasons, are not taking up the required job which would help commuters by saving time and fuel also.', '2017-11-28T04:23:20+0000', 'negative'),
('129115403803409_1439836342731302', 'For  an year or so the amber light in traffic signal almost got vanished! The amber (yellow) light allows the vehicles in the intersection, or those close to stop, to clear the intersection. Hence the light MUST remain amber long enough to allow all drivers who cannot stop have a chance to pass through the intersection safely on the amber.\nBut, nowadays, unfortunately the light becomes red from green without remaining amber for even a second thereby causing enough trouble to the drivers!', '2017-11-28T04:30:01+0000', 'negative'),
