('129115403803409_1440671436007617', 'Last Sunday, while coming from Lalbazar towards Central Metro station, suddenly a black Hyundai Fluidic Verna WB02AD5667 came out of parking, just opposite to Bhikharam Sweet shop, in immense pick up and hit a Black Bajaj Pulsar throwing away the rider and pillon. I was in front and watched the accident on my looking glass. Locals poured in to stop but the driver accelerated and ran away. I chased it and finally catch hold of the vehicle just before Kolutola Crossing. People started came in as soon as i stopped it and the driver and owner came out. In between heritage Tram from both the way came in. Being a responsible person and knowing the proper etiquette of driving, i started parking my Scorpio left side. Getting this chance, the driver took the charge again and violating signal took immediate right and local could not stop it again. I immediately called 100 and get connected to traffic control where i have mentioned all the details, thrice.\n\nI travel across on wheels and simply cant tolerate any non sense on the road. Earlier as well i saved few lives, chased vehicle at Rajarhat along with WB Police etc. But unfortunately there was none in any of the traffic post and the road is single way traffic, and took time to overtake and stop the vehicle.\n\nWith no whereabouts on the accident victims (hopefully badly injured), could you please let all of us know the status of this incident ? I was told but didn\'t receive any further communication / confirmation on whether the vehicle was caught, case no etc etc.\n\nImpact is pretty much visible from the video, no need to explain i think', '2017-03-21T09:08:22+0000', 'neutral'),
('129115403803409_1440767295988961', 'Today around 7:30pm when my car was taking right turn from bylane near Haldiram VIP Road towards Rajerhat connector, i was standing by with other cars in queue, you traffic personnel stopped me taking right turn and was forcing me to go straight whereas the other cars were allowed to take the right turn. In fact i was giving pass to a car carrying a patient so I was bit on left side. He abused and misbehaved with me. He took out an expensive and high end smart phone from his pocket, took picture of number plate of my car and threatened me to send me behind bars if i ask any questions. When asked he said his name is Nitai Das and said I can complaint about him where ever i wish. I managed to take his picture which is attached. This was a simple case of misuse of authority. Seperately I am writing to PM office.', '2017-05-27T18:36:41+0000', 'negative'),
