('129115403803409_1443000555748214', 'Please start taking the regular traffic jam at the stretch between Vidyasagar Setu and PTS more seriously. It is really frustrating to face this heavy traffic almost regularly for no reason. The awkward bus stop at Hastings (distance between hastings and pts is less than 200 mtrs) makes it even worse and the alipore bound vehicles are given way too much space for right turn hence blocking the large public buses to access the open straight stretch freely.', '2017-12-01T06:05:38+0000', 'positive'),
('129115403803409_1443067542408182', 'Duto jaygar kotha na bole parchi na.\n\n1. Alipur e Bhabani Bhabhan crossing.Jara okhane daily jatayat koren, janen nischoi, oi crossing kono police take na, crossing keu mane na, ekprokar amader gari dar koria rasta perote hy. er akta protikar korun. Pic dilam.\n\n2. Bidhan Sarani n Duff Street crossing. Bethune Church er kache. Police post ache, name matro. Kono police take na, Signal keu mane No parking zone e bike n gaari rakhe. Emnite khub jomjomat jayga, tarpopr gaari full speed e jay. Byabostha asa korchi.', '2017-12-01T07:58:32+0000', 'neutral'),
('129115403803409_1443118065736463', '(WB06M2227 has been prosecuted for STOP LINE VIOLATION, at LAKE GARDENS FLY OVER ROAD/DR. DEODHAR RAHAMAN ROAD/, at 21:30 hrs vide case no- crPC652166/17 dated 30-NOV-17. For online payment please visit https://kolkatatrafficpolice.net - TEAM KTP)\n\nSir I got this msg today and request you to send me the picture of the incident.', '2017-12-01T09:29:08+0000', 'neutral'),
('129115403803409_1443165699065033', 'Another reminder to KTP for the parking issue in Middleton Row.  Nothing has been done at all to disciple the rogues that park not only on both sides but also a third car waits illegally in second row waiting for parking. That leaves hardly space for one car to somehow pass while tackling the menace of pedestrians refusing to use the empty footpaths. \nThe revellers who come to park street have no right to endanger the lives of residents like me. There is enough parking further up in park street for them but due to collusion between police and parking agents we are netting made to wade through danger every evening\nPlease do not turn a blind eye and deaf ear to this issue and wait dir a tragedy to take place\nDO SOMETHING', '2017-12-01T10:48:44+0000', 'negative'),
('129115403803409_1443308135717456', 'While the whole world is striving to speed up things, why is KP hell bent on slowing down traffic at peak hours of the day? The place in the picture is of Shitalatala ( near Shapuipara) on the Prince Anwar Shah- Bypass connector. At 9:30 in the morning, this obstructions are kept right in the middle of the road. Wonder what\'s the use of these, apart from creating a traffic snarl and slowing down traffic. I understand that the place is congested, and vehicle speed needs to be controlled. That can easily be done by deploying a traffic constable who can monitor the job depending on the pedestrian pressure. But there is no reason why should the normal traffic flow be disturbed in this way...\n The same situation prevails again during the night, when such obstructions are put at all major crossovers through out the city starting 9pm. Does a megacity like Kolkata really slow down(read, go to sleep) at 9pm in the year 2017!!?!!?', '2017-12-01T14:16:59+0000', 'negative'),
('129115403803409_1443337715714498', 'Sir I got this message on 29th November, but my car was in my house that day. Request you to please verify the incident-WB26T6733 has been prosecuted for Light Signal Violation, at ALIPORE ROAD/BELVEDERE ROAD(NATIONAL LIBRARY)/, at 15:40 hrs vide case no- iiPC050423/17 dated 27-NOV-17. For online payment please visit https://kolkatatrafficpolice.net - TEAM KTP', '2017-12-01T14:56:08+0000', 'neutral'),
('129115403803409_1443348392380097', 'For your kind perusal\nPublic and traffic personnel should be educated regarding the amber light significance to stop giving cases regarding stop line violation and signal violation. The standard duration of amber light is 3 secs which is not maintained in many traffic signals of Kolkata ending up in rise in stop line violation and signal violation . Please maintain standards before giving cases .', '2017-12-01T15:10:06+0000', 'positive'),
('129115403803409_1443372589044344', 'Dear sir\nToday I received sms that my vehicle WB26X1638 has been prosecuted for over speeding vide case no crPC653576/17.\nBut as I was driving myself and I never exceeded speed 55 kmph.Please look into this matter.\nRegds\nAnindya Banerjee\n9830198642', '2017-12-01T15:44:44+0000', 'neutral'),
