('129115403803409_1443588832356053', 'There is no difference with wild dogs and KTP officers. They are Similar to each other as for example when a wild dog needs food he goes many places to get food and sometimes bites also and KTP officers also do same thing with innocent people. As for yesterday evening I am working in Swiggy I was wrongly entered in no right turn which is near moulalai crossing, one of KTP Constable came to me and said stop and get down from scooty ,as I did and behind me there was one more guy who also took a turn with me but that Constable left that guy. He told me to go to our senior officer I went to him he asked me for my license and asked me why did I enter in a no right turn. I told him that it was a mistake, but he made a fine I said ok,when I said that your Constable left that guy who also entered in no right turn he laughed at me . Both KTP officers laughed at me and the OC was only watching how he was dealing with me.\nI paid fine and and taken a pledge that from today and now I will never help any KTP officer whether he is a Constable or a senior SI or any Sergeant. Because there is no difference between with wild dogs and KTP officers. Yours faithfully.', '2017-12-01T20:34:24+0000', 'negative'),
('129115403803409_1443875918994011', 'Good morning, I reside just opposite to jadavpur police station. The songs are getting played from the ps ( jdv ps signal ) . This is very irritating for local residents like me. It is getting started at 8.15 am and continues till  around 8.30-9.00 pm. This is really annoying and hampering studies, official work etc. This is already a sound polluted zone due to vehicular movement and incessant honking. Goes up to 80- 85 decibels. So I would request you to turn the speakers towards jadavpur 8b / glass and ceramic angle as this is non residential area or reduce the sound/ regulate timings.\nI had informed the same earlier and prompt action was taken . Now it has started again. Request your intervention at earliest. As always thanks for the great work you are doing to keep city safe and sound is appreciated.', '2017-12-02T03:10:43+0000', 'positive'),
