('129115403803409_1459443424075242', 'False case registered by Kolkata  Police <ed><U+00A0><U+00BD><ed><U+00B1><U+00AE>\nThe mentioned case registered by Kolkata Police against my brother\'s bike which was not take out of garage after his demise on 27-03-2015. \nDispute raised twice to dctp@kolkatatrafficpolice.gov.in but no response till date.  Today when i called OC MTV Cell, TP 033 22505092,  the office who picked up had an extra case ready against the bike which as per his was registered  in 2014. \nMy sincere request to the department to sincerely check the records and get the investigation done as there are some corrupt official who just to achieve their target are registering false cases against  the innocent common man. \nHope to get a response this time.', '2017-03-27T06:00:43+0000', 'positive'),
('129115403803409_1462012277202461', 'Dear Sir, \nI have received this message from Kolkata Traffic stating violation of helmet norms. \nMessage read is as below\nWB01AA0165 HAS BEEN PROSECUTED FOR Without Helmet, AT SYED AMIR ALI AVENUE/BECK BAGAN ROW/, AT 13:35 HRS VIDE CASE NO- ggTW052518/17 DATED 11-MAR-17. FOR ONLINE PAYMENT PLEASE VISIT https://kolkatatrafficpolice.net - TEAM KTP\nThis is to inform you that my motorcycle wb01aa0165 was parked entire day at my residence in Moore avenue Kolkata 700040 on Saturday 11.03.2017.\nI will like to draw your attention as the case has been wrongly registered in my name and I am being asked to submit the challan fees. \nRequesting you to kindly look into the issue and resolve.\nRegards,\nAvinash Agarwal\n9874406280', '2017-03-27T03:26:05+0000', 'positive'),
('129115403803409_1462095490530874', 'I have complained against a Car which driven rashly. I have already mailed before but no response received yet. Please reply with the details of action taken by KP.', '2017-04-07T18:47:54+0000', 'neutral'),
('129115403803409_1464630880242694', 'Having not noticed, I had unknowingly parked in a clamping zone today in front of Ganguly Electrical to purchase certain items. As a result, I found my car clamped in accordance to the traffic rule when I came out of the shop after 10 mins. \n\nHowever, I have the following queries:\n\n1) why I have been charged for towing my car @Rs 200/- when the car was not towed at all and there was no towing vehicle in sight? Moreover, the receipt issued by the sergeant is in the name of Singh Crane Service (scan attached). How does the officer charge me for a service not availed and on a receipt of a 3rd party?\n\n2) there were another 5-6 other cars on the same lane 10 metres ahead parked by a garage and the same were exempted from clamping. Why? \n\n3) the pillion rider sitting with the officer on his official two wheeler and carrying the clamp keys was wearing an unstrapped half helmet (usually worn by traffic officials) which is not approved by law. Why the officer should not be fined for breaking the law himself?\n\nWhile I am sorry for having broken the law and have paid the penalty, I would look forward to your responses regarding the mentioned illegal activities.\n\nSumon Chakraborty \nMobile: 9007782203', '2017-05-17T06:50:11+0000', 'positive'),
