('129115403803409_1478756898839246', 'Taken at 8.56 am today near VIP Bazar on EM byepass. This bus was being driven in a very rash manner - thereby causing the other vehicles around it to sway either ways to avoid being hit by this bus. It never followed any single lane, and overtook from both sides randomly. I followed this bus from Ruby hospital crossing to Science city. The bus driver was least bothered about how the other vehicles were affected by his rash driving. Crossed many sergeants and traffic constables, who am sure witnessed this rash driving and yet remained mute spectators.\n \nMerely organising AWARENESS camps doesn\'t work. These drivers should be punished. Most of the cars on Kolkata roads get bruised by rash-driving autos, taxis and buses. They go away unpunished and we pay the price at our car\'s workshops.\nIf you ask me why I didn\'t complain to the sergeant on the spot, let me tell you that I have tried this earlier but they don\'t listen to the complaint. They would rather wait for an accident to happen before stepping forward. Hope someone can rein in these errant drivers.', '2018-01-11T05:03:49+0000', 'negative'),
