('129115403803409_1482377755143827', 'Please see the attached screenshot of SMS sent by you. Since the prosecuted vehicle is a 4 wheeler as you can verify from your records, kindly educate me about the traffic regulation under which I am required to wear a helmet while driving it. That the vehicle was  never out on the road on 24th night is another matter altogether. It is obvious what are doing:  you look up vehicles which have not been prosecuted for some time and issue them  citations. A friend who stays in Singapore has been getting notices, obviously for this reason. You are so pathetic it is not even funny.', '2018-01-15T14:20:09+0000', 'positive'),
('129115403803409_1482636378451298', 'Would like to bring to your notice two incidents that occurred on the same day (15-01-2018) where-in the problems of not having enough gadgets/equipments at the traffic guards’ disposal leads to wrongful fining of public vehicles.\n\nThe first incident occurred around 14:15 hours. I was heading towards Anwar-shah from Tollygunge tram depot. While crossing the signal right in front of the Eastern railway ticketing counter the signal turned to AMBER from GREEN while I was 5-10 meters away from the demarcated stop line. I was maintaining a decent speed of 50 kmph and attempting to sudden brake and stop within the stop line might have proved to be fatal. The traffic constable on duty at the time, Mr. Karmakar, stopped my vehicle (WB06J9678) and even after politely explaining to him that the light had just turned amber when I crossed the stop line he went ahead and handed over a ticket to me as per MVA 119/177 which is basically jumping a red signal. I am uploading a footage from my dashcam as evidence and also attaching a copy of the Receipt. Unfortunately, it is only while taking a picture of the receipt I noticed and to my surprise he had written the date wrong. (14-12-2017 instead of 15-01-2018). I would suggest checking surveillance camera of the area to confirm my claim.', '2018-01-15T20:50:38+0000', 'negative'),
('129115403803409_1482865518428384', 'There is a shuttle route from Sulekha Bridge to Rajarhat. Drivers of this route drive very rashly and endanger other cars and pedestrians in the roads. They overtake in the opposite lane and cause on coming traffic to completely stop. They also get on the EM By Pass at Singhabari overtaking other cars waiting at signal and causing a jam and then threaten other drivers and police.', '2018-01-16T04:39:32+0000', 'negative'),
('129115403803409_1482908331757436', 'Sunday night after my friend\'s wedding, a couple of my male friends and myself were en route to one of their house. We took an Uber cab and unfortunately had to make several stops so changing destinations and stops were made with the consent of the driver. Suddenly after a stop the driver decided to take another booking and instead of dropping us off to the relevant destination started small talking with us. Eventually we got into an argument and the driver asked us to get off in the middle of the road. We not having agreed to this, he relentlessly drove us to a random Kolkatatrafickpolice booth and started yelling and howling claiming that we were drunk.It was around 11 in the evening so we did not want to get off the cab and were trying to book another cab while inside. The Kolkatatrafickpolice started blaming us and instead of helping us took us to the police station at Parkcircus where we were treated like offenders. I was called a loose woman for drinking (i.e with my own money at my friend\'s place), smoking and having an opinion. We were detained and my male friends were threatened of being put behind the bars and thus had to pay the officers some money. After which I was constantly harassed by the male police officers and there were no legitimate or uniform female officers, but some random women without badges. I tried calling my friends to resolve the issue, but my father had to come in with money i.e INR 2500 to bail us out, which was not done legally but was given to the driver outside the station. While almost everything happened in front of the CCTV camera the transaction was made to happen outside. While we were harried, the Uber driver was given great treatment for having got the three of us to the station. I was the only woman in the station for the longest time and was being continuously shouted on for my drinking and fun-loving nature. My question is to the state; are we forever going to be scapegoat to the despotism and power-play of the bureaucracy? Is it always going to be a struggle for normal citizens to travel home safely at night, without being harassed by cab drivers and state officials? Is it so difficult for people to have a good time without being blamed for it. I mean we all work hard for existence and recreation, with a 3rd world state as ours, the government has no specific aids/policies for unemployed adults! So how is it on the Government who allows F.L shops to do great business across the country have issues with a woman drinking? How does a tax paying citizen like me feel safe in this city? How can I move around freely without feeling threatened?\n\n#uberisuntrustworthy #midnightharassmentsbyKolkataPolice #uberdrivermisbehaves #iwanttolearnaboutmyrights #whataretherightsofataxpayingcitizen', '2018-01-16T05:59:04+0000', 'negative'),
('129115403803409_1482936545087948', 'When is the next Lok Adalat at Alipore Court? Please let me know the date, time and address. My car\'s pending court cases can be settled only on Lok Adalat days or it can be settled on any other day? And also tell me whether pending court cases at other courts like Sealdah can be settled at Alipore Lok Adalat or not?', '2018-01-16T07:10:14+0000', 'positive'),
