('129115403803409_1492877624093840', 'Dear Sirs,\n\nI request your good selves to take note of the utter disregard for law exhibited by a Kolkata Police personnel, coupled with rash and negligent driving and road rage.\n\nI was going to the hospital today afternoon to care for my ailing father, and was waiting at the signal in front of Alipore Zoo on Alipore Road, to turn right towards National Library Gate on to Belvedere Road, when I noticed a Kolkata Police Jeep (WB 02 N 3119) blatantly violate the law by crossing the \"STOP\" line despite there being a Red signal (photo attached).  As clearly seen, other vehicles also followed suit and violated the \"STOP\" line, presumably instigated by the violation by the Police vehicle.\n\nHowever, not paying much attention to it thereafter, on the green signal, I proceeded on my way.  This particular Police vehicle was travelling on the right lane near the triangle near the Open Air Theatre, while I was on the left, but in front of the said Police vehicle.  Suddenly, this vehicle\'s driver decided to swerve left, and hit my vehicle on the right side of the rear bumper, causing damage to my vehicle, as also his.  Not only that, this personnel, who was not in uniform, disembarked from his vehicle and ran towards my car, hitting it multiple times on the glass window and hurled abuses at me, despite he hitting my vehicle from behind.  Moreover, the person also tried to damage my driver side rear view mirror and tried to break the driver side window when I opened it half way to try to talk to him.  But since I was travelling with a patient, I thought it fit to avoid any altercation / confrontation with a person clearly intoxicated with power of position / uniform, and thus left the scene.\n\nI, however, informed about this incident to Police Control Room at 100 immediately, who advised me to lodge a formal complaint before Alipore Police Station, which I shall do forthwith. \n However, I request you to kindly take note of such incidents and sensitise Police personnel, as it really pains to see such actions / behaviour from law enforcement personnel themselves, who set examples to us commoners to always uphold / abide by the law.', '2018-01-27T17:20:27+0000', 'positive'),
('129115403803409_1492914210728978', 'I had posted a complaint regarding incorrect prosecution on 14th April, 2017. KTP informed me that for necessary verification, my complaint has been forwarded to concerned office. I\'m yet to receive an update on that. Please revert back on my complaint and if I\'m found guilty provide me with the evidence to prove prosecution. If found guilty, like I mentioned on that day, I undertake to make necessary payments. Thank You!\nSHARING the screenshots below <ed><U+00A0><U+00BD><ed><U+00B1><U+0087><ed><U+00A0><U+00BC><ed><U+00BF><U+00BB>', '2017-05-05T17:11:03+0000', 'negative'),
('129115403803409_1494214457482322', 'Even no refusal cabs have preference... this no refusal cab refused me at minto park crossing and took another passenger right infront of me.. plz take necessary actions...', '2014-06-24T12:35:53+0000', 'neutral'),
('129115403803409_1494299883951614', 'I received a SMS from KTP on 29.01.2018 that my Car WB06H6738 has been prosecuted for Light Signal Violation on 26-01-2018 at Sahapur Road. However my car was at APOLLO HOSPITAL, 58 Canal Circular Rd, Kol-54, at the time of incidence as reported by KTP. Would request you to kindly check the footage and rectify the case.\n\nSudarsan Saha\n9836839965', '2018-01-29T11:15:03+0000', 'positive'),
('129115403803409_1494443353951009', 'Rake less driving by B. Badi Bag to Santoshpur mini bus WB 02F 4224. Could have met accident for harsh driving. After complaining to the bus conductor, refuse to listen us. Passengers life have no value to them. Why authorities don\'t take proper action on this bus services? Is it how we continue #safe_drive #save_life ... please take some action or waiting for fatal accident causes death and destruction? Also there were some school going kids on board.', '2017-05-06T06:05:18+0000', 'negative'),
('129115403803409_1494638817251054', 'We all are saddened by the Murshidabad accident and heartfelt condolences to the kith and kin of the deceased. One of the survivors has reported that the driver was talking on mobile when the accident took place. Talking on a mobile phone while driving a public transport and thus risking lives of so many is grievous and unforgivable offense. I know the accident site doesn\'t come under your jurisdiction, but you can introduce more stringent punishment for such offenses and other bodies can follow the suit. If a passenger sends a photo or video of a driver of a public transport talking on the mobile phone along with Reg no. while driving, you should launch immediately investigation. You can collaborate with CSTC, SBSTC, Private transporter ( including shared Taxi owners) to ensure that appropriate punishments are imposed when anyone is proven guilty.', '2018-01-29T19:31:26+0000', 'negative'),
