('129115403803409_1494956057219330', 'This car WB 04H 0490 came out from eco park crossing so fast when the traffic signal was green for narkel bagal bound vehicles,and traffic was moving at a steady space, it could have caused major accident. This is for your information and necessary action for kolkata/bidhannagar traffic police.\n#safedrivesavelife\n#uber\n#Kolkatatrafficpolice', '2018-01-30T04:04:57+0000', 'neutral'),
('129115403803409_1495015203880082', 'there are so many banners on the police traffic syand in the middle of the road  at garia crossing that cars coming from the 6 no route side are unable to see tge signal..i have posted the same previously too but you have not taken any action', '2018-01-30T05:42:20+0000', 'neutral'),
('129115403803409_1495058497209086', 'I was travelling back to Kolkata from Odhisa dated 28/1/18 with my family and my friend’s family in his car. Near Ulberia around 7.00 pm a Mahindra Truck ramped our Indica Vista car from behind during a narrow juncture where all vehicles were slowly moving. We chased the truck and stooped it but the driver was denying his fault as we seek help from the CIVIC volunteers and called the traffic guard. The traffic guard took all papers related to both of our vehicles which the truck driver initially denied. Later we were made to halt in an open space and the driver was arguing and instead we had collided with the truck. He was even threatening of ramping our car deliberately and its consequences for which I restored. The Traffic guard and the Civic volunteers helped us a lot to resolve the issue by calling the owner of the truck.  But it seemed to me that the driver was denying the fact of his negligence which resulted to the damage of the body of our car. Lastly after almost half an hour the owner decided to pay a nominal price of Rs. 2000 for the demur rage and instructed his driver, although the driver gave us 1500 rupees. To me it seems that the driver was intoxicated with cannabis, and was very provocative. Finally we left the incident place and the papers were handed over to us by the Traffic guard. The truck had a Nagaland number NL 01L 7543 and the driver was screening influence of its owners. To me, I think such drivers along with its owners must be brought under scrutiny for repeating or avoiding any major incidents in future.', '2018-01-30T07:04:32+0000', 'negative'),
