('129115403803409_1530599706988298', 'I have just received two no of Notice For Minor Traffic Violation vide Case No: 00TW287849/18 dated 6th February, 2018 time 10.46 am and vide Case No: 00TW295219/18 dated 14th February,2018 time 9.56 am both at Paddapukur Island on CIT Road and for the offence mentioned \'WITHOUT HELMET\'.. \n\nIn this regard I like to inform you it has been last 15 years, I have been traveling on the same Road twice daily for my occupation. And also as my home is at Tala Post office and office is at Golpark, I have to travel 15-17 km daily one sided through this particular route. My spouse has been my pillion every day since last 15 years. \n\nNow it is very surprising for myself I received a letter of noice from your end regarding non helmet cause, where I never ride a bike even 10 mts without helmet. For your information I also like to add I am a professional biker, who often out for long rides for 15-20 days all around the country. I have already visited several parts of our country with my same bike and that\'s why I am 200% passionate about my ride and always obey the rules and regulation.. It has been never in my life I ride the bike without Helmet. also as the mentioned location on CIT ROAD PADDAPUKUR ISLAND XING is just mid point of my 15-17 km journey and it is atleast 7-8 km far from my house it is impossible for me to ride without helmet.. \n\nAlso surprisingly the notice has not come for a single time, it was back to back and for the same offence. The mention dates are 6th and 14th February respectively.\n\nIn this regard I am requesting you to please check the recording of your CC camera on the same road at the same time to confirm my non offence..     \n\nYour early response in this matter highly expected..\n\nRegards,\n\nAvishek Bhattacharyya\n16/1 Banamali Chatterjee Street. Kolkata: 7000002\nVehicle No: WB01 AJ 4425\nVehicle Make: Royal Enfield 500 cc. Desert Strom\nHandheld: 9830362836.', '2018-03-10T08:03:50+0000', 'positive'),
('129115403803409_1530779453636990', 'This car driver was crossing parkcircus seven point crossing and headed towards PTS via AJC Bose Road flyover; he was taking call while passing the crossing.', '2018-03-10T12:58:09+0000', 'neutral'),
('129115403803409_1531016523613283', 'Wanted to give you a feedback about the horrible traffic conditions that we have been seeing in AJC Bose Road from 5th March\'18. You will ask me \"What\'s so special about 5th of March\'18?\". Sir, in case you are not aware, the Class XII CBSE Board Exams started on 5th March\'18. It was around 9:15 a.m. Traffic was at a standstill on AJC Bose Road. We saw students alighting from cars and running to reach the nearby Exam Centres....almost in tears. No special efforts by the Kolkata Traffic Police to ensure that the children are reaching the venue in time and in a calm, unhurried frame of mind. If I remember correctly, when the Madhyamik and Uchha Madhyamik Exams are held, we see the KTP giving their best performance in controlling the Traffic. We have also seen that loudspeakers are banned by the Kolkata Police. Unfortunately, this is not the case for the non-Madhyamik children. A couple of days ago, late in the night, there were loud firecrackers being burst for a marriage. How do you expect the children to study ? We had to call the KP and complain. Are the children appearing for ICSE/CBSE not children of West Bengal ? Or is it that the state does not care for them ? I leave you all with these thoughts which I am sure will be echoed by many parents.', '2018-03-10T17:48:58+0000', 'positive'),
('129115403803409_1531367740244828', 'Dear Sir,\n\nGood day! I jigar Malani was driving my car fm house at sarat Bose road mintoand was heading to a Elgin road.\n\nSince I have to take a u-turn to go fm sarat Bose road minto park crossing to Elgin road I did took it but u turn is not a signal violation (as I had asked police ji before). If it is then pls inform as this is  my daily route.\n\nPlease check my below challan copy and confirm me if I have broken the rule or not as this would in future help me as well. As daily being the same route I don\'t want to repeat the same offence unknowingly.\n\nYour support and guidance will be appreciated.\n\nWB02AK9073 has been prosecuted for STOP LINE VIOLATION, at SARAT BOSE ROAD/AJC BOSE ROAD/, at 09:35 hrs vide case no- crPC845131/18 dated 25-FEB-18. For online payment please visit https://kolkatatrafficpolice.net. For any query, contact dctp@kolkatatrafficpolice.gov.in - TEAM KTP\n\nI have already mailed the same thing trice but I have got not reply from the above email id so look forward for your guidance .\n\nThanks\n\nJigar Malani', '2018-03-11T02:45:20+0000', 'positive'),
