('129115403803409_1531771463537789', 'Want strict action to be against this parking person opposite westside camac Street, they charge 20 per hour and says this how it is, if you don’t pay I will file a complaint against your car number. Horrible behaviour, considering being a lady they behave in the worst way and this is the story now every where. The parking person concern charges 20,30 even 50 at various areas and argue that it is the rate. Also \nI called in the numbers which I noted earlier from hoarding by KP to contact for demanding excess money at 033-22624776 And they said please complaint in the nearest police station.\nAfter explaining him he said I will talk to the surgeon and banged the phone.\nThis parking system is getting corrupt and worst, A SERIOUS ACTION AND A BETTER AUTOMATED system should be involved.', '2018-03-11T12:57:45+0000', 'negative'),
('129115403803409_1532546190126983', 'A violation was noticed for NO PARKING against vehicle no. WB08D5817 at C R AVENEUE/VIVEKANANDA ROAD on 12-MAR-18 at 12:55 hrs. Please be cautious while driving. Download Kolkata Police Bondhu App (https://goo.gl/Mz9zZb) and Smart Parking App (https://goo.gl/aB2DJb) from Play store for hassle free parking  - Team KTP\n\nDear concern\nReceived this above text messages regarding the no parking case..\nShared the above photo of my vehicle parked on the footpath.\nI have a shop over there and just parked my vehicle in front of the shop.\nNow just help me like where i should park my vehicle.\nGetting this above text message from last two days.', '2018-03-12T07:34:40+0000', 'positive'),
('129115403803409_1532574166790852', 'Dear Sir \nReporting an incident that occurred yesterday around 11 PM a few metres away from Tollygunge Metro Station ... towards the Anwar Shah crossing ... I was driving my car and there was heavy traffic with lots of mini trucks parked in two lanes along the road ... I was moving slowly and trying to maintain a minimum distance from the car in front and still move on ... suddenly two people came in crossing the road at their own free will while the traffic police was waving frantically for us to move on ... I had to apply the brakes and let the jay walkers cross over and probably they got jolted at the sound of the brakes and literally abused me and said \"sab shala bhenge debo\", ... what\'s my fault ? Please let me know so that I can be a better driver and help you people in your efforts ... If you cannot then please introduce some rules and law so that we can drive safely too ... I was driving at a speed of 5kmph and I am sure you will know what was happening at that time at that place .. \n\nThanks and regards', '2018-03-12T08:17:17+0000', 'neutral'),
