('129115403803409_1542719822442953', 'Dear SIr\n\nI am Rajesh Jain, a resident of Middleton Apartments at 3 Middleton Row, Kolkata - 700071. \n\nI have to file a serious charge of illegal parking being done in Middleton Row right under the nose of Traffic Police in such a busy area like Park Street. Vehicles are dangerously allowed to be parked not only on both sides of the road but also perpendicular to the kerb on one side leaving virtually no space for more than one car to pass. ON top of this, there is always a vehicle standing in double line on both sides waiting to be parked. Everyday we residents have to wade through this zig zag to get to our home. And imagine what happens when traffic becomes both sides after 10 pm. It is almost impossible to get home without putting up a fight for driving space. The drive of a mere 100 meters takes almost 10 minutes due to such illegal parking being operated by virtual touts under the nose of the police.\n\nLast Sunday only, I called up the South traffic guard  at 10.05 pm when my car did not get any space to pass in order to reach home from Camac Street end. The young sergeant who came to check and bring the touts to task did a very good job and even prosecuted vehicles. Even after his instructions, it continues to be the same scene everyday without any change.\n\nEven as early as 7 pm you can find vehicles parked both sides and in the manner explained above. It has become a nightmare to enter our street after 7 pm due to this issue.\n\nI urge you to take stern steps to stop vehicles being parked perpendicular to the curb and on both sides of the street. The revellers of Park Street have no right to disturb the peace of the residents and you must use your authority to help protect our right to peaceful living\n\nThanks and regards\n\nRajesh Jain', '2018-03-22T16:18:10+0000', 'negative'),
