('129115403803409_1543508655697403', 'Again booked by false case at parama island..case ID AX18S883255 dated 22March-18 by Officer Pranab Debnath. \n\nI was heading towards Garia from Salt Lake Sec.-V. I was at the stop line at Mathpukur crossing, then started driving towards parama island. The road was complete empty cause of a bit long traffic signal and that time I had pushed the throttle of my bike ( It was my fault ) But I\'m not sure what exactly the speed was. Yes it was above 50kmph I agree.\n\nNear to island my bike speed was around 30-35km hardly because used to face short red signal at island.Officer was standing at the middle of the road to stop me. Stopped the bike, gave him the DL and he told me that I was speeding. Yes I must be prosecuted. My DL got ceased and I\'m prosecuted.\n\nReturning home I was checking the case detail and found that I was prosecuted by dangerous driving offence.\n\nAccording to Officer it was 80 to 83 kmph but today when I approached to him just to say \'Sir that case was overspeeding case then he told me your speed near 100 so I\'m confused and I think Officer too . He also added that I will decide what case I should apply and informed me that \'he told me couple of time that I was driving dangerously when his body cam was on recording yesterday so that he can file the case.\n\nPreviously on same island they had forced a TATA ACE to enroll MONTHLY ( not sure what are the terms and conditions of MONTHLY ) for not having all documents. I was carrying some furniture to home. That was pathetic.\n\nStill I say not all sergent or officers are like so. There are lots of officers are there in KTP doing their duty honestly and friendly to commuters . Hats off to all of them but I\'m sorry for those officers who file false case.\n\nThank You Kolkata Traffice Police.\n\nI WILL ASK EVERY COMMUTERS TO HAVE DASH CAM AND HELMET CAM IF POSSIBLE SO THAT YOU CAN AVOID SUCH FALSE CASE', '2018-03-23T13:32:25+0000', 'negative'),
