('129115403803409_1550953958286206', 'Dear Sir,\n\nMy car bearing registration number WB24AN6181 has been damaged on 31.Mar.2018 at around 7:15PM by an auto rickshaw with registration number WB04D8074. I was standing at the traffic signal at Muchi Bazar travelling from HUDCO crossing towards Gouribari. The autorickshaw hit my car from behind and damaged right side of back bumper of the car.\n\nLocation of the accident - https://www.google.co.in/maps/place/22%C2%B035\'39.9%22N+88%C2%B023\'03.8%22E/@22.5944332,88.3756202,15z/data=!3m1!4b1!4m14!1m7!4m6!1m3!2m2!1d88.384376!2d22.594413!1m0!3e0!3m5!1s0x0:0x0!7e2!8m2!3d22.5944142!4d88.3843746\n\nI also tried to lodge a complaint at Ultadanga Police Station, but the person refused to lodge the case saying the location is under the jurisdication of Maniktala Police Station.\n\nRequest to file a case against the same auto richshaw for damaging the car and request compensation from the owner of the autorickshaw for the same damage.\n\nThanking you,\nAnirban Seth\nPh. 9051484825', '2018-03-31T14:16:31+0000', 'negative'),
('129115403803409_1551101238271478', 'When someone doesn\'t wear seat belt, there is a fine imposed. When you overspeed there is a fine imposed. When you break a signal , there is a fine imposed. However when a vehicle hits you and you ask police for help, I wonder if this is being taken care of. Rather the driver of the accused vehicle is left - license is only being taken from him - i think to get that released a nominal amount is to be paid.\n\nAround 3 pm , due to heavy traffic, my car was standing in the signal of Santragachi. All of a sudden a Chevrolet WB12C 9638 bumped into my vehicle causing damage to the bonet. I reached out for help to the traffic inspector present and he asked me to settle it with the driver / file a complaint in the near police station / or he can take his license. For a moment I felt if I was playing KBC.I didn\'t have much time to negotiate considering the fact that I had to rush to hospital for a family emergency. \n\nWB12C 9638 had passengers inside , and they even threatened not to talk to police . The driver said the car belongs to him, on questioning him he conveyed that the passengers have hired the car. I questioned the Inspector that if the car is hired why Commercial No plate was not used and private number plate was present. To this surprisingly he said that probably they are family members (amazing). Anyway I had to leave due to paucity of time but this seriously made me think is this justifiable? When we break rules we are being penalised but when someone else is at fault why are we not assisted. \n\nNot sure if I need to raise this separately to Howrah Traffic. License no of the driver : WB - 088979. \n\nWould be helpful if you can assist.', '2018-03-31T17:36:03+0000', 'negative'),
