('129115403803409_1561023387279263', 'Hello, I received an sms for Light signal Violation on 9th April 2018. However my car was never out of the garage for this given day. Could you verify the case (WB06F3163)? Also, if the case stand please provide photographic evidence. Thanks.', '2018-04-11T10:23:19+0000', 'neutral'),
('129115403803409_1561144180600517', 'Dear sir,  \nI have received the this case paper today  by post. I have sold this car on the month of May 2014,  I personally visited Motor Vehicles Office (Saltlake, Sector 5) for the the transfer of ownership but suddenly today I received this document. \nPlease help me with a solution. \n\nCase No.  : crPC890900/18 \nDated : 17.03.2018 \nTime : 22.35 \nU/S code : 112/183(2) MVA', '2018-04-11T13:22:54+0000', 'positive'),
('129115403803409_1561438960571039', 'This person.. Whose bike is saying that he works for Kolkata Police.. There is a label of Police under number plate. He had break lots of signals today between 16:00 pm to 17:00 pm.. Kindly check any CCTV footage of EM Bypass. From patuli to towards Science City.. even he broke all the signals every time.. Sometimes i have overcrossed him just to take the picture. #Patuli , #Ajaynagar #Abhishikta, #BeforeAjaynagar #PanchannaGram .. these singnals for sure.. if the person is not Getting fined.. Then why we janata janardan.  Last day at 6th April i have been faced a case which has been taken from the cctv footage.. when no car was there.. 12:00 am.. Then i broke a signal.. but i have been fined.. Kindly check Kolkata Police.. hope u will take care of it.', '2018-04-11T18:08:30+0000', 'negative'),
('129115403803409_1561449700569965', 'Dear Sir / Madam,\n\nOn 7th April 2018, I had been challaned for violating the traffic signal under section 119/177 at the Teghoria Crossing. I had paid the fine of Rs. 100 through GRIPS online and had submitted the receipt at Baguiati Traffic Police guard, but the concerned officer did not return my DL. He said that for a couple of sections they have the power to suspend my license for 3 months, to counter which, I have to attend the same venue to meet the Inspector of Police with the plea to release my DL. He handed over a paper to me, which he said is a notice, but refused to sign the document. I want to know, if this procedure is indeed valid or should I book a complaint at the appropriate authorities as the notice paper do not have a signature of the concerned authority, but does have, although very much unrecognizable, the Ashok Stambh stamp with Baguiati Traffic Guard imprinted around it. Can you please provide the clarification and suggest to me the next course of action?', '2018-04-11T18:25:43+0000', 'neutral'),
('129115403803409_1561554140559521', 'If you are in Kolkata and driving in New town area, please be careful (specially after dark). Due to road repair and metro rail work, lots of diversions (without any sign / light) are there and everyone is confused about which way to take. To make matters worse, almost invisible 18 wheel trucks without any light might pop out of no where! Lots of these trucks have broken / no light at all and many people are loosing lives as these trucks are impossible to detect!', '2018-04-11T20:43:59+0000', 'negative'),
('129115403803409_1561738187207783', 'Day before yesterday at Lords crossing on anwar shah around at 7.50pm i saw an action by traffic surgent which calls for good appreciation. \nA woman with a mobile phone pressed on her left ear was crossing the road from lake gardens side to golf green side. The signal was green and traffic was moving from golf green side to anwar shah road. The cars were coming with a right hand turn. The chatting busy woman with mobile wasn\'t looking at the car approaching. She was at the blind spot of a Driver. Traffic surgent standing nearby YELLed at maximum possible and stopped her. Scolded her. Had not happened, she would have been hit by the approaching car. But fault was hers. I saw everything. But she was real insensitive person. She continued to talk on her mobile and never bothered to thank the surgent who saved her. \nI thank surgent for his good job. Let others too do it......', '2018-04-12T01:40:03+0000', 'neutral'),
('129115403803409_1561793357202266', 'Sir,\nIn a rough analysis of secondary data like newspaper reports or other media reports, I found the following points causing recurring incidents on the road. Statistical analysis were done using PSPP software. Upon generalisation following have been found.\n\n1) No or the least idea about the Blind Spots in large Vehicles like Bus etc.\n2) No or minimum idea wrt safe distance from vehicles in front or behind \n3) No minimal use of full body Protection Gears by the Bikers especially on highways.\n4)No or minimal use of RVM by bikers and ORVM by cars\n5) No or minimal use of signal for changing lanes or slowing down even for turning right or left\n6) Big vehicles occupy the fast lane or right most lane on highways. Left side overtaking becomes must then for others.\n\nN.B.\nMy study was done for educational purpose. But findings may be important for you.\nDisclaimer: As secondary data sources have been used for the study the findings are just indicative and more study is needed based on more accurate and authentic data sources like cctv footages, dash cam recordings etc.', '2018-04-12T02:58:28+0000', 'neutral'),
('129115403803409_1561865237181131', 'Mr.  Arun Kumar, respected Sargent of kolkata traffic police, at Minto park crossing at 12 noon approximately,  not even bothered to take any action against a cab driver for hitting my car and after that also threatening of calling 15-20 guys to beat me, in front of him. Even telling me to complain wherever I want to go and complain.', '2017-04-24T06:57:01+0000', 'negative'),
