('129115403803409_1562935257088076', 'Menace of Bus overtaking near NewTown Bus Stand - Everyday while going from office (sec V to Newtown) through Biswas Bangla road, I have seen the buses simply race and overtake dangerously they do not care whether other vehicles are there on the road. Yesterday same incident happened with me - a white public bus with no WB 25 F 2910 was just about to crush my WagonR just before NewTown Signal. And this happens everyday - the buses race among one another for picking up office staffs from DLF 1. There are cctv cameras and police posts at this crucial junction but no action is taken against these speeding buses....yesterday I have lodged a complain in Bidhan Nagar Traffic Control....hope the traffic wardens posted in New Town takes note of this...before another accident occurs.', '2018-04-13T06:45:03+0000', 'negative'),
('129115403803409_1562996740415261', 'Sir \ni love kokata police \ni believe i maintained Rules \natleast Wearing Helmet and not breaking Signals\nI crossed Maniktalla when i saw Signal Green which i believe it means *Go*\nThe problem was with the Signal and Not with me ... i crossed when it waa Green and with a two seconds it became Red ....\nFirst of All how can It gives Green Signal for 2 seconds and i m sure A VIP person was about to pass thats why Local Cop was too much On pressure .... \nIf u can prove me i broke the signal then i will quit riding bikes !!!\n9830324101 is my mobile no.\ni repeat i love Kolkata police and i dont break rules !!!', '2018-04-13T08:01:43+0000', 'negative'),
('129115403803409_1563141100400825', 'Crtw262608/18 case dated 18 March 18\n\nThere are two stop lines , on the first stop line the words STOP is written over which gives an impression that the final stop line is the one where yellow reflectors are planted. I feel that the yellow reflectors are placed for this purpose to help drivers identify the exact stop line.\nWill be cautious in future\n9433922172', '2018-04-13T10:54:43+0000', 'neutral'),
