('129115403803409_1568541423194126', 'I want to report a serious incident that just now took place at Metro Cash & Carry bus stop near Mukundapur.\n\nA Garia Station - Baghbazar bound bus almost ran over a bunch of people standing at the bus stop, just so it could overtake our office bus and beat the yellow blinking signal ahead of us. And eventually, it broke the signal which had turned red by then.\n\nI took this photo of that bus from my office bus near Ruby. The number plate is visible in this photo. It\'s WB19 H 4101.\n\nThe driver of the Garia Stn.-Baghbazar bus was threatening our office bus driver using disturbing and unthinkably abusing language, since he could not get past ahead of our bus and beat the signal, even after seeing lady associates sitting in our bus. When our driver tried to draw his attention towards the fact that ours is an office bus and lady associates are sitting inside, the driver of the public bus became more furious and started abusing our driver and the helper badly.\n\nTherefore, I would really like to request you to look into this matter with utmost importance as we could have easily ended up experiencing a dangerous accident which could have taken many lives out there.\n\nAgain, it\'s a GARIA STATION - BAGHBAZAR route bus of WHITE COLOR and with a number plate of WB19 H 4101.\n\n#KolkataTrafficPolice', '2018-04-19T04:06:37+0000', 'negative'),
