('129115403803409_1570520486329553', 'Respected Sir/Madam,\n\nFirst of all, I would like to Thank Kolkata Traffic Police  for the amazing works that you do EVERYDAY. We, Kolkatans know very well how hard and tidious job it is to maintain traffic flow consisting of thousands of vehicles this smoothly, in a big city like Kolkata. \n\nI would like to draw your attention towards an issue that I have faced recently and would request you to take action which would be in the best interest of daily commuters and Kolkata Traffic Police. While travelling from Apollo Hospital (my work place) to Beliaghata (my home) through the service lane (parallel to em bypass), I was stopped by a Traffic Police at Kadapara/Hyatt end and I was informed that its one way ie, the lane can only be used while going from Kadapara towards Apollo Hospital.\n\nI did notice a guard rail at Kadapara end but no such thing or No Entry sign is there at Apollo/Mani Square end which is leading to great confusion.\n\nSince no clear cut no entry instruction is there at Apollo end of the service road, vehicles are taking that lane and going towards Kadapara only to find that the lane is indeed one way. \n\nIt is my ernest request to you to provide clear instruction and information of No Entrt at Apollo end so that we commuters are not misguided and the traffic flow remains smooth.\n\nThanks and regards,\n\nNilanjan Majumdar \n\nPS - The traffic police understood my confusion regarding the situation and was kind enough to let me go without any prosecution and I am thankful to him and Kolkata Traffic Police for that.  <ed><U+00A0><U+00BD><ed><U+00B8><U+008A><ed><U+00A0><U+00BD><ed><U+00B8><U+008A><ed><U+00A0><U+00BD><ed><U+00B8><U+008A>', '2018-04-21T09:38:40+0000', 'positive'),
