('129115403803409_1571436906237911', 'Dear Sir,\n\nThis is to bring your notice that my car - A Red Maruti Swift ZXi has suffered major damage  on the right rear bumper after being hit by a Renault Kwid Car at Kadapara Signal.I would like to say that NEITHER OF THE TWO CARS WERE AT FAULT.If someone were to blame, it is the incorrigible traffic system put into place by the Kolkata Traffic Police,whereby the traffic lights abruptly turn from GREEN to RED and vehicles start plying across the roads. If I were to continue driving even after the signal went red,it could have caused a major accident or even if that could be averted,the traffic sergeants are always eager to penalise the civilians for any rule breaking. My point in writing such a post is two-fold:\n\na. Please review your traffic signalling system and make necessary modifications to the same,so as to avoid such accidents which can cause major damage to life and property of law-abiding tax-paying citizens.\n\nb.Who will bear the cost of the damage to the two cars, when neither one were at fault.This is a clear case of negligent traffic signalling system and thereby expect KTP to take necessary actions.\n\nThis post might never get published or any action might not even be taken,but going by the promptness shown by Kolkata Police on its FB page, I am still hoping against hope that this reaches the authorities and necessary actions and precautions be taken by the authorities, so as to not repeat such incidents in the future.\n\nRegards,\nSoumyadip Basu', '2018-04-22T08:50:09+0000', 'positive'),
