('129115403803409_1572374966128870', 'I was travelling through New Alipore by own car (WB02AL0568). There is a maze of roads from JL Sarani to New Alipore and I followed natural flow of traffic (read autos & commercial pickup tricks). I was stopped by this guy who told that I\'ve just entered a \'No Entry\' . I apologized and informed that I\'ve just bought a car and unfamiliar with this area. It never occurred to me that the road on which so many vehicles were plying is a NO ENTRY. There is no prominent No Entry board displayed.(In this age at least KP can afford a red light or display board or Notice board). The guy himself is positioned not to guide the traffic to intended way but to entrap unsuspecting citizens and extract bribe from them. He gave me 2 options i.e to settle the matter there & then by pay Rs. 100 to him in cash or he\'ll book me in serious offence. I said \"taking a wrong turn cannot be a serous offence. I\'ll just turn around and go my way. I\'ll not pay any btibe\". He didn\'t gave his name and rank despite several requests so I\'m not able to provide the same however his picture is attached herewith. To sum up I\'ve following complaints:-\n1. Please guide your force to regulate and guide the traffic rather than setting up traps for hapless citizens to fall into and pay you bribes. Kindly sensitize them towards public service rather than looting the public.\n2. Please look at his appearance. Unshaven, unclean, torn uniform, top buttons of shirt open. He looks more like a ruffian than a policeman. Your men need to learn to respect their job & position first before they learn public service.\n\nHope there is some improvement after this feedback.\n\nThanks.', '2017-05-24T04:15:50+0000', 'negative'),
