('129115403803409_1573487262699542', 'Along the right lane of 4 no bridge of Park Circus towards 7 point crossing, a lot of train passengers rush to catch their connecting train but there is no foothpath and it may cause fatal accident anytime as vehicles move very fast along this lane keeping no space left for the pedestrians.\nApart from that, there is a underpass on which there is no parapet wall and commuters may fall down on the underpass road while they rush to catch the trains..\nHence I request you to look into the matter and make necessary arrangement for the safety of train commuters.', '2018-04-24T14:57:01+0000', 'negative'),
('129115403803409_1573493776032224', 'Why is driving rules in Kolkata are different from other states? I wanted to highlight & bring your attention about the lane discipline & traffic norms that must be observed on roads of every city. I have been driving in this city for more than a year now & I have hardly found anyone observing lane discipline. Private buses hover on the roads as if they own it, they stop anywhere and everywhere whether its the right most lane or on the signal line even if the lights are green to pick up passengers as if they are mimicking of a garbage truck to pick up garbage. The buses don\'t just reach the commuters to their destination but they also take part in a race with other buses to get more passengers & I have had many close calls & near misses just for these idiotic driving culture. The autorickshaws here are in so hurry & hungry for passengers that the side indicators are a mystery for them, they never bothers to indicate whether they are about to stop or make a lane change. In heavy traffic areas the 2 lane roads are automatically converted to 3-4 lanes by the magical powers of the drivers in the city making the flow completely clogged after the lights are green. Many trucks of that belongs to Kolkata municipality are way out of order to be driven on city roads, blowing out heavy smoke with rusted & broken chassis parts. Lastly I would like to admit that the vehicles or bikes that belongs to the Kolkata police are least bothered to take a halt on red lights. As per the rules only the emergency vehicles have the privilege to jump the lights that too if it is necessary and required. The buses violating the rules are never stopped for a challan or penalty because I have personally seen them giving tips to the sergeant incharge of a crossing. Well its a good way to earn though. Just wearing a helmet won\'t make the roads safe, lane discipline is mandatory too as the helmets and seatbelts. I had been driving on the roads of Mumbai since 2005 and the people driving there are just awesome. The traffic department in Mumbai has the courtesy to stop at red lights. As of my experience its a worst nightmare to drive in Kolkata. There are many possible ways to make the roads of Kolkata a much better and safe place to drive with very little contributions from the drivers as well as the traffic police. I\'m sure that this post is not going to change anything but still I thought to write, because we never know if 2-3% people of the city may start practising the actual campaign \"SAFE DRIVE SAVE LIFE\".', '2018-04-24T15:05:55+0000', 'positive'),
('129115403803409_1573533412694927', 'Hello kolkata traffic police, \n\nI just want to know Sir why rashbehari to taratalla auto guys take fair according to their wish. There is no rule for them. Normal fair for rashbehari to taratala is 12 but normally they charge 15 after 7 pm but just bcoz no one is saying anything they have started taking 20 . Please look into matter and take proper action. The auto number is wb04 e2939', '2018-04-24T16:00:54+0000', 'positive');
